8-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|title='Black Panther,' 'Walking Dead' Rule Saturn Awards Nominations|accessdate=March 16, 2018|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 15, 2018|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6xwc1azco?url=http://variety.com/2018/film/news/saturn-awards-nominations-2018-black-panther-walking-dead-1202727752/|archive-date=March 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| Emma Watson\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Production Design|Best Production Design]]\n| Sarah Greenwood\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n| Jacqueline Durran\n| {{win}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Seattle Film Critics Society]]\n| December 18, 2017\n| Best Costume Design\n| Jacqueline Durran\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://seattlefilmcritics.com/|title='Blade Runner 2049' Leads the 2017 Seattle Film Critics Society Nominations|last=Seattle Film Critics Society Editors|date=December 11, 2017|work=[[Seattle Film Critics Society]]|accessdate=December 11, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911180917/http://seattlefilmcritics.com/|archivedate=September 11, 2017}}</ref><br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://seattlefilmcritics.com/2017/12/18/get-named-best-picture-2017-seattle-film-critics-society/|title=\"Get Out\" Named Best Picture of 2017 by Seattle Film Critics Society|date=December 18, 2017|website=Seattle Film Critics Society|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171212163705/http://seattlefilmcritics.com/2017/12/11/blade-runner-2049-leads-the-2017-seattle-film-critics-society-nominations/https://web.archive.org/web/20171219120239/http://seattlefilmcritics.com/2017/12/18/get-named-best-picture-2017-seattle-film-critics-society/|archivedate=December 12, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[St. Louis Gateway Film Critics Association Awards 2017|St. Louis Film Critics