 Fantasy Actor]]\n| Dan Stevens\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actress \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie: Fantasy Actress]]\n| Emma Watson\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Villain|Choice Movie Villain]]\n| Luke Evans\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie Ship\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Emma Watson and Dan Stevens\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Choice Liplock\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Choice Scene Stealer\n| Josh Gad\n| {{nom}}\n|- \n| rowspan=\"2\"| Choice Hissy Fit\n| Luke Evans\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Dan Stevens\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[16th Visual Effects Society Awards|Visual Effects Society Awards]]\n| February 13, 2018\n| Outstanding Virtual Cinematography in a Photoreal Project\n| Shannon Justison, Casey Schatz, Neil Weatherley and Claire Michaud for \"[[Be Our Guest]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-visual-effects-society-awards-nominations-list-full-1067888|title=Visual Effects Society Awards: 'Apes,' 'Blade Runner 2049' Lead Feature Nominees|work=Hollywood Reporter|first=Carolyn|last=Giardina|date=January 16, 2018|accessdate=January 16, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116220634/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-visual-effects-society-awards-nominations-list-full-1067888|archive-date=January 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Awards 2017|Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| December 8, 2017\n| Best Motion Capture Performance\n| Dan Stevens\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dcfilmcritics.com/awards/|title=The 2017 WAFCA Awards|work=[[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association]]|date=December 7, 2017|accessdate=December 6, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312055647/http://www.dcfilmcritics.com/awards/|archivedate=March 12, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Production Design\n| Sarah Greenwood and Katie Spencer\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Women Film Critics Circle]]\n| December 17, 2017\n| Best Family Film\n| ''Beauty and the Beast''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=The 2017 Women Film Critics Circle (WFCC) Nominations|url=https://www.nextbestpicture.com/latest/the-2017-women-film-critics-circle-wfcc-nominations|last=Neglia|first=Matt|accessdate=December 13, 2017|date=December 12, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171213010140/https://www.nextbestpicture.com/latest/the-2017-women-film-critics-circle-wfcc-nominations|archivedate=December 13, 2017}}</ref><br /><ref>{{cite web|title=The 2017 Women Film Critics Circle (WFCC) Winners|url=https://www.nextbestpicture.com/latest/the-2017-women-film-critics-circle-wfcc-winners|last=Neglia|first=Matt|accessdate=December 25, 2017|date=December 22, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171226130500/https://www.nextbestpicture.com/latest/the-2017-women-film-critics-circle-wfcc-winners|archivedate=December 26, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Controversies==\n===Gay character===\nControversy erupted after director [[Bill Condon]] said there was a \"gay moment\" in the film, when LeFou briefly waltzes with Stanley, one of Gaston's friends.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/03/20/beauty-and-the-beast-gay-moment-audience-reaction/99407168/ |title='Beauty and the Beast's 'gay moment' may have been much ado about nothing |newspaper=USA Today |date=March 20, 2017 |accessdate=March 21, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910204317/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/03/20/beauty-and-the-beast-gay-moment-audience-reaction/99407168/ |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref> Afterwards in an interview with [[Vulture.com]], Condon stated, \"Can I just say, I'm sort of sick of this. Because you've seen the movie\u2014it's such a tiny thing, and it's been overblown.\" Condon also added that ''Beauty and the Beast'' features much more diversity than just the highly talked-about LeFou: \"That was so important. We have interracial couples\u2014this is a celebration of everybody's individuality, and that's what's exciting about it.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/03/bill-condon-on-directing-beauty-and-the-beast.html |title=Bill Condon on Beauty and the Beast, His Musical Influences, and Lindsay Lohan's Plan for The Little Mermaid |publisher=Vulture |date=March 15, 2017 |accessdate=March 19, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170419051553/http://www.vulture.com/2017/03/bill-condon-on-directing-beauty-and-the-beast.html |archivedate=April 19, 2017  }}</ref> GLAAD president and CEO Sarah Kate Ellis praised the move, stating, \"It is a small moment in the film, but it is a huge leap forward for the film industry.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/glaad-beauty-and-the-beast-gay-moment-disney/|title=GLAAD president: \"Beauty and the Beast\" foes are \"outliers\"|author=Ned Ehrbar|publisher=CBS News|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170419051558/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/glaad-beauty-and-the-beast-gay-moment-disney/|archivedate=April 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn Russia, [[Vitaly Milonov]] agitated the culture minister for banning the film,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/global/russia-ban-beauty-and-the-beast-josh-gad-gay-lefou-1202002198/ |title=Russia May Ban Disney's 'Beauty and the Beast' Over Gay Character |work=Variety |date=March 4, 2017 |accessdate=March 5, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304203350/http://variety.com/2017/film/global/russia-ban-beauty-and-the-beast-josh-gad-gay-lefou-1202002198/ |archivedate=March 4, 2017  }}</ref> but instead it was given a 16+ rating (children under the age of 16 can only be admitted to see it in theaters with accompanying adults).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/03/06/beauty-and-the-beast-russia-lawmaker-ban/ |title=Russia won't ban Beauty and the Beast\u2014but will have an age restriction |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=March 6, 2017 |accessdate=March 7, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910205642/http://ew.com/movies/2017/03/06/beauty-and-the-beast-russia-lawmaker-ban/ |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref> Additionally, a theater in [[Henagar, Alabama]] did not screen the film because of the subplot.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/beauty-and-the-beast-alabama-theater_us_58b9a6f7e4b05cf0f400427b |title=Alabama Theater Won't Show 'Beauty and the Beast' Because of Gay Subplot |work=The Huffington Post |accessdate=March 3, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170306104238/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/beauty-and-the-beast-alabama-theater_us_58b9a6f7e4b05cf0f400427b |archivedate=March 6, 2017  }}</ref> In [[Malaysia]], the [[Film Censorship Board of Malaysia|Film Censorship Board]] insisted the \"gay moment\" scene be cut, prompting an indefinite postponement of its release by Disney, followed by their decision to withdraw it completely if it could not be released uncensored.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/03/13/beauty-and-the-beast-release-postponed-for-internal-review/|title=Beauty and the Beast release postponed for 'internal review'|last=Cheang|first=Michael|date=March 13, 2017|accessdate=March 15, 2017|website=The Star Online|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170314040844/http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/03/13/beauty-and-the-beast-release-postponed-for-internal-review/|archivedate=March 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/beauty-and-the-beast/news/a823340/disney-pulls-beauty-and-the-beast-from-cinemas-in-malaysi-until-further-notice/ |title=Disney pulls Beauty and the Beast from cinemas in Malaysia 'until further notice' |website=Digital Spy |date=March 13, 2017 |accessdate=March 13, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910204933/http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/beauty-and-the-beast/news/a823340/disney-pulls-beauty-and-the-beast-from-cinemas-in-malaysi-until-further-notice/ |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Disney refuses to cut 'gay moment' from 'Beauty and the Beast' for Malaysia|website=Malay Mail Online|accessdate=March 15, 2017|date=March 15, 2017|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/disney-refuses-to-cut-gay-moment-from-beauty-and-the-beast-for-malaysia|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910205012/http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/disney-refuses-to-cut-gay-moment-from-beauty-and-the-beast-for-malaysia|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> The studio moved the release date to March 30, to allow more time for Malaysia's censor board to make a decision on whether or not to release the film without changes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disney-wont-cut-beauty-beast-gay-moment-malaysia-censors-986609|title=Disney Defies Malaysia Censors, Won't Cut 'Beauty and the Beast' Gay Moment|author=Mia Galuppo|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 15, 2017|accessdate=March 16, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910205050/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disney-wont-cut-beauty-beast-gay-moment-malaysia-censors-986609|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> The distributors and producers then submitted an appeal to the Film Appeal Committee of Malaysia, which allowed the film to be released without any cuts and a [[Film censorship in Malaysia#Rating system|P13 rating]] on the grounds that \"the gay element was minor and did not affect the positive elements featured in the film\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/malaysia-clears-release-beauty-beast-gay-moment-intact-report-987588|title=Malaysia Clears Release of 'Beauty and the Beast,' with 'Gay Moment' Intact|author=Patrick Brzeski|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 21, 2017|accessdate=March 21, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910205127/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/malaysia-clears-release-beauty-beast-gay-moment-intact-987588|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/03/29/film-appeals-committee-decision-to-release-beauty-and-beast/|title=Film Appeal Committee's decision to release Beauty and the Beast|newspaper=The Star Online|date=March 21, 2017|accessdate=March 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910205221/http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/03/29/film-appeals-committee-decision-to-release-beauty-and-beast/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> In [[Kuwait]], the movie was withdrawn from cinemas by [[Cinescape|National Cinema Company]] which owns most of the cinemas in the country. A board member of the company stated that the Ministry of Information's censorship department had requested it to stop its screening and edit it for things deemed offensive by it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-39337844|title=Beauty and the Beast pulled from cinemas in Kuwait|publisher=BBC|date=March 21, 2017|accessdate=March 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328145707/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-39337844|archivedate=March 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe film also received criticism over its portrayal of LeFou, as many felt that it was used as a way of teasing LGBT+ viewers without providing adequate representation, with his \"exclusively gay moment\" being three seconds of him dancing with another man at the end of the film.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://screenrant.com/beauty-beast-power-rangers-gay-representation/|title=How Beauty and the Beast & Power Rangers Cheated Gay Fans|date=April 2, 2017|work=Screen Rant|access-date=October 21, 2017|language=en-US|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021111628/http://screenrant.com/beauty-beast-power-rangers-gay-representation/|archivedate=October 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Belle and the Beast's relationship===\nDisney has sought to portray Belle as an empowered young woman,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Watkins|first1=Gwynne|title='Beauty and the Beast' Featurette Makes a Case for Feminist Belle|url=https://www.yahoo.com/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-featurette-makes-a-case-for-feminist-belle-180620182.html|accessdate=March 26, 2017|publisher=Yahoo Movies|date=March 2, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170419051635/https://www.yahoo.com/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-featurette-makes-a-case-for-feminist-belle-180620182.html|archivedate=April 19, 2017}}</ref> but a debate questioning whether it is possible for a captor to fall in love with their prisoner, and whether this is a problematic theme, has resulted.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Williams|first1=Zoe|title=Beauty and the Beast: feminist or fraud|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/mar/19/beauty-and-the-beast-feminist-or-fraud|accessdate=March 26, 2017|newspaper=The Guardian|date=March 19, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170419051751/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/mar/19/beauty-and-the-beast-feminist-or-fraud|archivedate=April 19, 2017}}</ref> As was the case with the original animated film, one argument is that Belle suffers from [[Stockholm syndrome]] (a condition that causes hostages to develop a psychological alliance with their captors as a survival strategy during captivity). Emma Watson studied whether Belle is trapped in an abusive relationship with the Beast before signing on and concluded that she does not think the criticism fits this version of the folk tale.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Blasberg|first1=Derek|title=Cover Story: Emma Watson, Rebel Belle|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/02/emma-watson-cover-story|accessdate=March 27, 2017|work=Vanity Fair|date=February 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170228194205/http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/02/emma-watson-cover-story|archivedate=February 28, 2017}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=August 2018}}<ref>{{cite news|last1=Breznican|first1=Anthony|title=Beauty and the Beast: Emma Watson addresses questions over Beast relationship|url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/02/16/beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-belle-beast-relationship/|accessdate=March 26, 2017|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=February 16, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910210130/http://ew.com/movies/2017/02/16/beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-belle-beast-relationship/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> Watson described Stockholm Syndrome as \"where a prisoner will take on the characteristics of and fall in love with the captor. Belle actively argues and disagrees with [Beast] constantly. She has none of the characteristics of someone with Stockholm Syndrome because she keeps her independence, she keeps that freedom of thought\", also adding that Belle defiantly \"gives as good as she gets\" before forming a friendship and romance with the Beast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/02/16/beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-belle-beast-relationship/ |title=Beauty and the Beast: Emma Watson addresses questions over Beast relationship |accessdate=August 9, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910210130/http://ew.com/movies/2017/02/16/beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-belle-beast-relationship/ |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref>\n\nPsychiatrist [[Frank Ochberg]], who was responsible for defining the term \"Stockholm syndrome\", said he does not think Belle exhibits the trauma symptoms of prisoners suffering from the syndrome because she does not go through a period of feeling that she is going to die.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Watkins|first1=Gwynne|title=Does Belle From 'Beauty and the Beast' Suffer From Stockholm Syndrome? We Asked an Expert.|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/does-belle-from-beauty-and-the-beast-suffer-from-stockholm-syndrome-we-asked-an-expert-175449990.html|accessdate=March 26, 2017|publisher=Yahoo Movies|date=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910210202/https://www.yahoo.com/news/does-belle-from-beauty-and-the-beast-suffer-from-stockholm-syndrome-we-asked-an-expert-175449990.html|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> Some therapists, while acknowledging that the pairing's relationship does not meet the clinical definition of Stockholm syndrome, argue that the relationship depicted is dysfunctional and abusive and does not model healthy romantic relationships for young viewers.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Durvasula|first1=Ramani|title=Does Belle from Beauty and The Beast Have Stockholm Syndrome?|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5zyYzdsmeBU|accessdate=March 26, 2017|publisher=Screen Junkies|date=March 23, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170407104600/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5zyYzdsmeBU|archivedate=April 7, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Simon|first1=Rachel|title=The 'Beauty and the Beast' Relationship Isn't \"Stockholm Syndrome,\" No Matter How Screwed Up It May Be|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/the-beauty-the-beast-relationship-isnt-stockholm-syndrome-no-matter-how-screwed-up-it-may-be-44217|accessdate=March 26, 2017|magazine=Bustle|date=March 16, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910210257/https://www.bustle.com/p/the-beauty-the-beast-relationship-isnt-stockholm-syndrome-no-matter-how-screwed-up-it-may-be-44217|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> Following this viewpoint, Constance Grady of [[Vox (website)|Vox]] wrote that [[Jeanne-Marie Leprince de Beaumont]]'s ''Beauty and the Beast'' was a fairy tale originally written to prepare young girls in 18th-century France for [[arranged marriage]]s, and that the power disparity is amplified in the Disney version.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Grady|first1=Constance|title=Is Beauty and the Beast \"a tale as old as Stockholm syndrome\"? Depends how you read it.|url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2017/3/23/15000768/beauty-and-the-beast-feminist-stockholm-syndrome|accessdate=March 26, 2017|publisher=Vox|date=March 23, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910210439/https://www.vox.com/culture/2017/3/23/15000768/beauty-and-the-beast-feminist-stockholm-syndrome|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> Additionally, Anna Menta of ''[[Elite Daily]]'' argued that the Beast does not apologize to Belle for imprisoning, hurting, or manipulating her, and that his treatment of Belle is not painted as wrong.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Menta|first1=Anna|title=The 'Beauty and the Beast' Love Story Doesn't Hold Up To Emma Watson's Feminism|url=http://elitedaily.com/entertainment/film/beauty-and-the-beasts-abusive-relationship-emma-watson/1828119/|accessdate=March 26, 2017|website=Elite Daily|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910210528/http://elitedaily.com/entertainment/film/beauty-and-the-beasts-abusive-relationship-emma-watson/1828119/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Future==\n===Potential follow-up film===\nShortly after the release of the film, [[Sean Bailey]] said that [[Walt Disney Pictures]] will \"explore possible [live-action] spin-off and prequel scenarios\" for animated and live-action Disney films, including ''Beauty and the Beast''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-sean-bailey-disney-emma-watson-1202047710/|title=Sean Bailey On How Disney's Live-Action Division Found Its 'Beauty and the Beast' Mojo|website=Deadline|date=March 21, 2017|first=Mike|last=Fleming Jr.|access-date=April 28, 2019|archive-url=https://archive.li/20170910100558/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-sean-bailey-disney-emma-watson-1202047710/|archive-date=September 10, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Both [[Dan Stevens]] and [[Emma Watson]] expressed interest in reprising their roles in potential sequel or prequel to the film.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-sequel-dan-stevens-sex-comedy-permission-tribeca-1202393018/|title=Dan Stevens on 'Beauty and the Beast' Sequel Talk, Tribeca Sex Comedy 'Permission'|magazine=Variety|date=April 22, 2017|first=Ramin|last=Setoodeh|access-date=April 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190430124608/https://variety.com/2017/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-sequel-dan-stevens-sex-comedy-permission-tribeca-1202393018/|archive-date=April 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1830510/emma-watson-brought-up-a-potential-beauty-and-the-beast-sequel-idea-again|title=Emma Watson Brought Up A Potential Beauty and the Beast Sequel Idea Again|website=Cinema Blend|date=January 9, 2018|first=Adam|last=Holmes|access-date=April 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190428043706/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1830510/emma-watson-brought-up-a-potential-beauty-and-the-beast-sequel-idea-again|archive-date=April 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Spin-off/prequel series===\nOn March 6, 2020, it was reported that [[ABC Signature Studios]] is developing a prequel limited series to the film focused on Gaston and LeFou, for [[Disney+]].<ref name=\"Disney+Series\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/beauty-beast-prequel-series-works-at-disney-1282859|title='Beauty and the Beast' Prequel Series in the Works at Disney+ (Exclusive)|date=March 6, 2020|first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|access-date=March 7, 2020m|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Luke Evans]] and [[Josh Gad]] will reprise their roles from the film, and will executive-produce the series alongside [[Eddy Kitsis]] and [[Adam Horowitz]], with Gad, Kitsis and Horowitz serving as showrunners and writers for the series.<ref name=\"Disney+Series\"/> [[Alan Menken]] is in talks to return as composer for the series.<ref name=\"Disney+Series\"/>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n*{{official website|http://movies.disney.com/beauty-and-the-beast-2017}}\n*{{IMDb title|2771200}}\n*{{Rotten Tomatoes|beauty_and_the_beast_2017|Beauty and the Beast}}\n*{{Box Office Mojo|beautyandthebeast2017}}\n*{{AllMovie title|601458}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=''Beauty and the Beast''|state=collapsed\n|list1=\n{{Beauty and the Beast}}\n{{Disney's Beauty and the Beast}}\n{{Disney Princess}}\n{{Disney's live-action adaptations of animated franchises}}\n{{Alan Menken|state=collapsed}}\n{{Howard Ashman|state=collapsed}}\n{{Tim Rice|state=collapsed}}\n{{Bill Condon}}\n{{Stephen Chbosky}}\n{{MTV Movie Award for Best Movie}}\n}}\n{{Portal bar|Disney|Film|United States}}\n\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:2017 3D films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy adventure films]]\n[[Category:American musical fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:American romantic fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American romantic musical films]]\n[[Category:Beauty and the Beast (franchise)]]\n[[Category:Censored films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Disney film remakes]]\n[[Category:Films featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:Films about curses]]\n[[Category:Films about royalty]]\n[[Category:Films about shapeshifting]]\n[[Category:Films based on adaptations]]\n[[Category:Films based on Beauty and the Beast]]\n[[Category:Films based on multiple works]]\n[[Category:Films based on works by Linda Woolverton]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Alan Menken]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Bill Condon]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 18th century]]\n[[Category:Films set in castles]]\n[[Category:Films set in France]]\n[[Category:Films shot at Shepperton Studios]]\n[[Category:Films using computer-generated imagery]]\n[[Category:American historical romance films]]\n[[Category:IMAX films]]\n[[Category:Mandeville Films films]]\n[[Category:Motion capture in film]]\n[[Category:Film remakes]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Evan Spiliotopoulos]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Stephen Chbosky]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Pictures films]]\n[[Category:American historical musical films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Beauty and the Beast\n| image          = Beauty and the Beast 2017 poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Bill Condon]]\n| producers      = {{Plainlist|\n* [[David Hoberman]]\n* [[Todd Lieberman]]\n}}<!-- please do not add other producers; these two are the only listed per The Hollywood Reporter -->\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Stephen Chbosky]]\n* [[Evan Spiliotopoulos]]\n}}\n| based on       = {{Plainlist|\n* {{Based on|[[Walt Disney Animation Studios|Disney]]'s ''[[Beauty and the Beast (1991 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]''|[[Linda Woolverton]]}}<ref name=PressKit>{{cite web|url=http://www.wdsmediafile.com/media/BeautyAndTheBeast/writen-material/BeautyAndTheBeast58b624ab24380.pdf|title=Beauty and the Beast Press Kit|website=wdsmediafile.com|publisher=Walt Disney Studios|format=PDF|accessdate=April 7, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422170239/http://www.wdsmediafile.com/media/BeautyAndTheBeast/writen-material/BeautyAndTheBeast58b624ab24380.pdf|archive-date=April 22, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* {{Based on |''[[Beauty and the Beast]]''|[[Jeanne-Marie Leprince de Beaumont]]}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.york.ac.uk/news-and-events/features/2017/beauty-and-the-beast-remake-2017/|title=Beauty and the Beast remake: A traditional tale with a modern twist|work=University of New York|date=March 13, 2017|accessdate=April 14, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414162617/https://www.york.ac.uk/news-and-events/features/2017/beauty-and-the-beast-remake-2017/|archivedate=April 14, 2017}}</ref>\n<!--Do not change. This is what is credited in the film. Any alteration must be properly sourced.-->\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Emma Watson]]\n* [[Dan Stevens]]\n* [[Luke Evans]]\n* [[Kevin Kline]]\n* [[Josh Gad]]\n* [[Ewan McGregor]]\n* [[Stanley Tucci]]\n* [[Audra McDonald]]\n* [[Gugu Mbatha-Raw]]\n* [[Ian McKellen]]\n* [[Emma Thompson]]\n}}<!--Only the principal cast based on the poster should be credited.-->\n| music          = [[Alan Menken]]\n| cinematography = [[Tobias A. Schliessler]]\n| editing        = Virginia Katz\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Walt Disney Pictures]]\n* [[Mandeville Films]]\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Walt Disney Studios<br />Motion Pictures]]<!--DO NOT CHANGE-->\n| released       = {{Film date|2017|2|23|[[Spencer House, London|Spencer House]]|2017|3|17|United States}}\n| runtime        = 129 minutes<!-- Theatrical runtime: 129:07 --><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/beauty-and-beast-2017|title=''BEAUTY AND THE BEAST (PG)''|work=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|date=February 16, 2017|accessdate=March 7, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303115920/http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/beauty-and-beast-2017|archivedate=March 3, 2017}}</ref>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $160\u2013255 million<ref name=\"BOM\" /><ref name=2017FFS>{{Cite report |date=August 8, 2018 |title=2017 Feature Film Study |url=https://www.filmla.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/2017_film_study_v3-WEB.pdf |publisher=FilmL.A. |page=23 |access-date=August 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180809153120/https://www.filmla.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/2017_film_study_v3-WEB.pdf |archivedate=August 9, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=ForbesBudget/>\n| gross          = $1.264&nbsp;billion<ref name=\"BOM\" />\n}}\n\n'''''Beauty and the Beast''''' is a 2017 American [[Musical film|musical]] [[romantic fantasy]] film directed by [[Bill Condon]] from a screenplay written by [[Stephen Chbosky]] and [[Evan Spiliotopoulos]]. Co-produced by [[Walt Disney Pictures]] and [[Mandeville Films]],<ref name=PressKit /><ref name=\"thr\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-teaser-tops-star-897032|title='Beauty and the Beast' Teaser Tops 'Star Wars: Force Awakens' in First Day|last=McClintock|first=Pamela|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=May 24, 2016|accessdate=May 25, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170404042941/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-teaser-tops-star-897032|archivedate=April 4, 2017}}</ref> it was filmed entirely in Britain with predominantly British principal actors. The film is a [[live-action]] adaptation of Disney's [[Beauty and the Beast (1991 film)|1991 animated film of the same name]], itself an adaptation of [[Jeanne-Marie Leprince de Beaumont]]'s 18th-century [[Beauty and the Beast|fairy tale]].<ref name=\"Penske Business Media\">{{cite web|last1=Erbland|first1=Kate|title='Beauty and the Beast' Is a Technological Marvel, But for Its Actors, the Challenge was Daunting|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-technology-dan-stevens-guga-mbatha-raw-1201794115/|website=IndieWire|publisher=Penske Business Media|accessdate=March 23, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324083829/http://www.indiewire.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-technology-dan-stevens-guga-mbatha-raw-1201794115/|archivedate=March 24, 2017}}</ref> It features an [[ensemble cast]] including [[Emma Watson]] and [[Dan Stevens]] as the eponymous characters, with [[Luke Evans]], [[Kevin Kline]], [[Josh Gad]], [[Ewan McGregor]], [[Stanley Tucci]], [[Audra McDonald]], [[Gugu Mbatha-Raw]], [[Ian McKellen]], and [[Emma Thompson]] in supporting roles.<ref name=\"digital-spy\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/feature/a795376/beauty-and-the-beast-cast-trailer-release-date-everything-you-need-to-know/ |title=Beauty and the Beast 2017 cast, trailer, release date and everything you need to know |work=Digital Spy |date=December 1, 2016 |accessdate=January 26, 2017 |author=Fletcher, Rosie |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304045404/http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/feature/a795376/beauty-and-the-beast-cast-trailer-release-date-everything-you-need-to-know/ |archivedate=March 4, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA live-action ''Beauty and the Beast'' remake was first announced in April 2014, with Condon hired to direct it; Watson, Stevens, Evans, and the rest of the cast signed on between January and April 2015. [[Principal photography]] lasted from May to August 2015, and took place at [[Shepperton Studios]] in England. With an estimated budget of around $255&nbsp;million, it is one of the [[List of most expensive films|most expensive films ever made]]. The film premiered at [[Spencer House, London|Spencer House]] in London on February 23, 2017, and was theatrically released in the United States in standard, [[Disney Digital 3-D]], [[RealD 3D]], [[IMAX]], and [[IMAX 3D]] formats, along with [[Dolby Cinema]] on March 17, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Phillips |first1=Ian |last2=Acuna |first2=Kristin |url=http://www.techinsider.io/disney-movies-until-2019-2015-8 |title=Disney announced all its movies coming in the next 4 years\u2014here's what you have to look forward to |publisher=[[Tech Insider]] |date=October 27, 2015 |accessdate=November 3, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20160105060342/http://www.techinsider.io/disney-movies-until-2019-2015-8 |archivedate=January 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n''Beauty and the Beast'' received generally positive reviews from critics, with many praising its faithfulness to the original animated film, as well as elements from the Broadway musical, performances of the cast (particularly Watson and Stevens), visual style, musical score, songs, costume design, and production values, though criticism was drawn toward some of the character designs and its excessive similarity to the original.<ref name=\"BeautyandtheBeastReview\" /><ref name=\"BeautyandtheBeastCriticReview\" /> The film grossed over $1.2&nbsp;billion worldwide, becoming the highest-grossing live-action musical film, making it the [[2017 in film#Highest-grossing films|second-highest-grossing film of 2017]], and the [[List of highest-grossing films|<!--This is the peak position the film attained, not the current, don't adjust!-->10th<!--This is the peak position the film attained, not the current, don't adjust!-->-highest-grossing film of all time]]. The film received four nominations at the [[23rd Critics' Choice Awards]] and two nominations at the [[71st British Academy Film Awards]]. It also received [[Academy Award]] nominations for [[Academy Award for Best Production Design|Best Production Design]] and [[Academy Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]] at the [[90th Academy Awards]]. A spin-off/prequel TV series is in development.\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, plot summaries for feature films should be between 400 to 700 words. -->\n\nA beautiful enchantress disguised as an old beggar woman arrives at a castle during a ball and offers the host, a cruel and selfish prince, a rose in return for shelter from a storm. When he refuses, she reveals her identity. As punishment for the prince's lack of compassion, the enchantress transforms him into a beast and his servants into household objects, then erases the castle, himself and his servants from the memories of their loved ones and everyone else in the town. She casts a spell on the rose and warns the prince that the spell will only be broken if he learns to love another, and earn their love in return before the last petal falls, or he will remain a beast forever.\n\nSome years later, in the small town of Villeneuve, Belle, the book-loving daughter of an inventor named Maurice, dreams of adventure. She constantly brushes off advances from Gaston, an arrogant former soldier, as he is not the type of man Belle wishes to marry. On Maurice's way to a convention and lost in the forest, he seeks refuge in the Beast's castle, but the Beast imprisons him for stealing a rose from his garden as a gift to Belle. When Maurice's horse returns without him, Belle ventures out in search for him, and finds him locked in the castle dungeon. Belle tricks both her father and the Beast by asking for a simple hug goodbye from her father, she pushes him out and locks herself in the dungeon. The Beast agrees to let her take her father's place and forces Maurice to leave immediately.\n\nBelle befriends the castle's servants, who invite her to a spectacular dinner. When she wanders into the forbidden west wing and finds the rose, the Beast scares her into the woods. She is ambushed by a pack of wolves, but the Beast rescues her, becoming injured in the process. As Belle nurses his wounds, a spark develops between them. The Beast shows Belle a gift from the enchantress, a book that transports readers wherever they want. Belle uses the book to visit her childhood home in Paris, where she discovers a [[Plague doctor costume|plague doctor mask]] and realizes that she and her father were forced to leave when her mother succumbed to the [[Bubonic plague|plague]].\n\nIn Villeneuve, Maurice fails to convince the other villagers of the Beast and Belle's imprisonment. Gaston, seeing rescuing Belle as an opportunity to win her hand in marriage, agrees to help Maurice. When Maurice learns of his ulterior motive and rejects him, Gaston abandons him to be eaten by the wolves. Maurice is rescued by the town hermit Agathe, but when he tells the townsfolk of Gaston's crime and is unable to provide solid evidence, Gaston convinces them to send Maurice to an insane asylum.\n\nAfter sharing a romantic dance with the Beast, Belle discovers her father's predicament using a magic mirror. The Beast releases her to save Maurice, giving her the mirror to remember him with. At Villeneuve, Belle reveals the Beast in the mirror to the townsfolk, proving her father's sanity. Realizing that Belle loves the Beast, a jealous Gaston claims she has been charmed by dark magic, and has her thrown into the asylum carriage with her father. He rallies the villagers to follow him to the castle to slay the Beast before he curses the whole village. Inside the asylum carriage, Belle tells her father that she knows what happened to her mother and showed him the rose rattle she took from her magical visit to their old, abandoned home. Maurice and Belle escape, and Belle rushes back to the castle.\n\nDuring the battle, Gaston abandons his companion LeFou, who then sides with the servants to fend off the villagers. Gaston attacks the Beast in his tower, who is too depressed to fight back, but regains his spirit upon seeing Belle return. He defeats Gaston, but spares his life before reuniting with Belle. However, Gaston fatally shoots the Beast from a bridge, which then collapsed as the castle began to crumble, leading Gaston to fall to his death. The Beast then dies as the last petal falls, and the servants become inanimate. \n\nAs Belle tearfully professes her love to the Beast, Agathe reveals herself as the enchantress and undoes the curse, repairing the crumbling castle, and restoring the Beast and servants to their human forms and to the villagers' memories. The Prince and Belle host a ball for the kingdom, where they dance happily.\n\n==Cast==\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Emma Watson]] as [[Belle (Beauty and the Beast)|Belle]], a young benevolent [[Bibliophilia|bibliophile]] who develops feelings for the Beast and begins to see the humanity within him.\n** Daisy Duczmal portrays an infant Belle. \n* [[Dan Stevens]] as [[Beast (Beauty and the Beast)|Beast]], a cold-hearted, selfish, unkind prince who is transformed into a beast and forced to earn back his humanity by learning to truly love and be loved in return, as well as to give rather than take. Stevens portrays the character through [[motion-capture acting|motion-capture]].<ref name=\"StevensCast\" /><ref>{{cite web |first=Karen |last=Earnest |url=http://movies.mxdwn.com/news/dan-stevens-to-star-in-the-man-who-invented-christmas/ |title=Dan Stevens to Star in 'The Man Who Invented Christmas' |publisher=Movies.mxdwn.com |accessdate=March 2, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115071204/http://movies.mxdwn.com/news/dan-stevens-to-star-in-the-man-who-invented-christmas/ |archivedate=November 15, 2016  }}</ref>\n** Adam Mitchell{{ref|a}} portrays the younger version of the prince.\n* [[Luke Evans]] as [[Gaston (Beauty and the Beast)|Gaston]], a narcissistic and arrogant hunter and veteran of the [[French Royal Army (1652\u20131830)|French Royal Army]] who is willing to go as far as it takes to have Belle as his [[trophy wife]].\n* [[Kevin Kline]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Maurice|Maurice]], Belle's protective widowed father who works as a music box maker and an artist.<ref name=\"ReleaseThompsonKline\" />\n** Jolyon Coy portrays the young Maurice.\n* [[Josh Gad]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Le Fou|LeFou]], Gaston's flamboyant and long-suffering sidekick who bolsters his friend's ego but gets very little in return.<ref name=\"GadCast\" />\n* [[Ewan McGregor]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Lumi\u00e8re|Lumi\u00e8re]], the Beast's charismatic [[ma\u00eetre d']] who has been transformed into a [[candelabra]].<ref name=\"McGregorCast\" />\n* [[Stanley Tucci]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Maestro Cadenza|Maestro Cadenza]], the neurotic court composer and Madame de Garderobe's husband who has been transformed into a [[harpsichord]].<ref name=\"TucciCast\" />\n* [[Audra McDonald]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#The Wardrobe|Madame de Garderobe]], a world-renowned opera singer and Cadenza's wife who has been transformed into a [[wardrobe]].<ref name=\"McDonaldCast\" />\n* [[Gugu Mbatha-Raw]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Featherduster|Plumette]], one of the castle maids and Lumi\u00e8re's lover who has been transformed into a [[feather duster]].<ref name=\"RawCast\" />\n* [[Ian McKellen]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Cogsworth|Cogsworth]], the Beast's gruff but loyal [[majordomo]] and the head of the household staff who has been transformed into a [[mantel clock]].<ref name=\"McKellenCast\" />\n* [[Emma Thompson]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Mrs. Potts|Mrs. Potts]], the castle's motherly head [[Housekeeper (domestic worker)|housekeeper]] who has been transformed into a [[teapot]].<ref name=\"ReleaseThompsonKline\" /> \n* [[Hattie Morahan]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#The Enchantress|Agathe]], an impoverished [[hermit]] and resident of Villeneuve who, in reality, is the enchantress responsible for cursing the Prince.<ref name=\"releasedateportal\">{{cite web |url=http://www.releasedateportal.com/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-release-date-2/ |title=Beauty and the Beast Release Date \u2013 2017 |publisher=Releasedateportal.com |date=June 30, 2016 |accessdate=March 2, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226132633/http://www.releasedateportal.com/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-release-date-2 |archivedate=February 26, 2017  }}</ref> Morahan also narrates the prologue.\n** Rita Davies portrays the enchantress in her beggar woman form. The film was released [[List of works published posthumously#2010s|posthumously]] after Davies' death.\n* [[Nathan Mack]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Chip Potts|Chip]], Mrs. Potts' plucky son who has been transformed into a [[teacup]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Gavin |first=Michael |url=http://www.insidethemagic.net/2016/08/photo-first-look-at-dan-stevens-beast-prince-form-from-disneys-live-action-beauty-and-the-beast-movie/ |title=PHOTO: First look at Dan Stevens Beast (prince form) from Disney's live-action 'Beauty and the Beast' movie! |publisher=Inside the Magic |date=August 27, 2016 |accessdate=March 2, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226093154/http://www.insidethemagic.net/2016/08/photo-first-look-at-dan-stevens-beast-prince-form-from-disneys-live-action-beauty-and-the-beast-movie/ |archivedate=December 26, 2016  }}</ref>\n* [[Adrian Schiller]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Monsieur D'Arque|Monsieur D'Arque]], the sly warden of the local asylum who is bribed by Gaston to have Maurice institutionalized.<ref name=\"releasedateportal\" />\n* [[Gerard Horan]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Jean Potts|Monsieur Jean Potts]], an absent-minded [[Pottery|potter]] and resident of Villeneuve who is later revealed to be Mrs. Potts' husband and Chip's father.\n* [[Haydn Gwynne]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Clothilde|Clothilde]], a [[fishmonger]] and resident of Villeneuve who is later revealed to be Cogsworth's wife.\n* [[Michael Jibson]] as the Tavern Keeper, the owner and keeper of Villeneuve's local tavern where Gaston and the village residents drink.\n* [[Ray Fearon]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#The Bookseller|P\u00e8re Robert]], Villeneuve's local chaplain who encourages Belle to borrow the books in the chapel's meager library.\n* Sophie Reid, [[Rafa\u00eblle Cohen]], and Carla Nella as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#The Triplets|the Village Lasses]], a trio of women who fawn over Gaston and have a jealousy for Belle.\n* Jimmy Johnston, Dean Street, and Alexis Loizon as Tom, Dick, and Stanley, a trio of men who serve as Gaston's henchmen.\n* Zoe Rainey as Belle's mother, Maurice's late wife who contracted the [[plague (disease)|plague]] and died when Belle was an infant.\n* [[Clive Rowe]] as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Chef Bouche|Cuisinier]], the castle's head [[chef]] who has been transformed into a [[Kitchen stove|stove]].\n* Gizmo as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Sultan|Frou-Frou]], Maestro Cadenza's and Madame de Garderobe's pet [[Yorkshire Terrier]] who has been transformed into a [[footstool]].\n* Thomas Padden as [[List of Disney's Beauty and the Beast characters#Coat Rack|Chapeau]], the prince's [[valet]] who has been transformed into a [[coat rack]].\n* Tom Turner{{ref|b}} as The King, the prince's father who, following his wife's death, raised his son to be just as selfish and arrogant as he was.\n* Harriet Jones as The Queen, the prince's mother who died of an illness when he was a child.\n* Dale Branston as Villeneuve's residential baker.\n* Chris Andrew Mellon as Nasty Headmaster, the unnamed headmaster of an all boys school in Villeneuve that disapproves of Belle teaching a young girl how to read.\n* Vivian Parry as the Village Lass' mother, an unnamed seamstress.\n}}\n\n[[Stephen Merchant]] also appeared in the film as Monsieur Toilette, a servant who was turned into a toilet. This character was cut from the film, but is featured in the deleted scenes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/06/01/beauty-and-the-beast-deleted-scene-reveals-monsieur-toilette/ |title=Beauty and the Beast deleted scene reveals Monsieur Toilette |accessdate=December 7, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606025231/http://ew.com/movies/2017/06/01/beauty-and-the-beast-deleted-scene-reveals-monsieur-toilette/ |archivedate=June 6, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n===Cast notes===\n{{note|a}} In the initial theatrical release, Mitchell was miscredited as Rudi Goodman in the cast, but listed under his real name in the soundtrack credits\n\n{{note|b}} In the initial theatrical release, Turner is miscredited as [[Henry Garrett (actor)|Henry Garrett]] in the cast.<ref name=\"OriginalDaysInTheSun\">{{cite web|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/beauty-and-the-beast-deleted-scene/|title=Bill Condon Reveals 'Beauty and the Beast' Mistake in Alternate 'Days in the Sun' Sequence|accessdate=September 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902093831/http://www.slashfilm.com/beauty-and-the-beast-deleted-scene/|archive-date=September 2, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nPreviously, Disney had begun work on a film adaptation of the [[Beauty and the Beast (musical)|1994 Broadway musical]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Marmiroli|first=Adriana|url=http://www.lastampa.it/2009/06/05/spettacoli/alan-menken-adesso-musical-anche-in-italia-tpFNsKZZjpc7PLwUeVEkKM/pagina.html|title=Alan Menken Adesso musicalanche in Italia|work=[[La Stampa]]|date=June 5, 2009|accessdate=May 21, 2015|language=Italian|trans-title=Alan Menken musicals now in Itaty|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150524013613/http://www.lastampa.it/2009/06/05/spettacoli/alan-menken-adesso-musical-anche-in-italia-tpFNsKZZjpc7PLwUeVEkKM/pagina.html|archivedate=May 24, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Hill|first=Jim|url=http://jimhillmedia.com/blogs/jim_hilll/archive/2009/07/01/hollywood-bets-big-on-beast-considers-remake-of-my-fair-lady.aspx|title=Hollywood bets big on 'Beast,' considers remake of 'My Fair Lady'|work=Jim Hill Media|date=July 1, 2009|accessdate=May 21, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090704035305/http://jimhillmedia.com/blogs/jim_hilll/archive/2009/07/01/hollywood-bets-big-on-beast-considers-remake-of-my-fair-lady.aspx|archivedate=July 4, 2009}}</ref> However, in a 2011 interview, composer [[Alan Menken]] stated the planned film version of the ''Beauty and the Beast'' stage musical \"was canned\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.denofgeek.com/movies/725326/alan_menken_interview_tangled_movie_scores_musicals_enchanted_2_snow_queen_and_more.html|last=Brew|first=Simon|title=Alan Menken interview: Tangled, movie scores, musicals, Enchanted 2, Snow Queen and more|accessdate=January 22, 2011|date=January 11, 2011|publisher=[[Dennis Publishing|Den of Geek]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130121113312/http://www.denofgeek.com/movies/725326/alan_menken_interview_tangled_movie_scores_musicals_enchanted_2_snow_queen_and_more.html|archivedate=January 21, 2013}}</ref>\n\nBy April 2014, [[Walt Disney Pictures]] had already begun developing a new [[List of Disney live-action remakes of animated films|live-action version]] of ''[[Beauty and the Beast (1991 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' after making other live-action fantasy films such as ''[[Alice in Wonderland (2010 film)|Alice in Wonderland]]'', ''[[Maleficent (film)|Maleficent]]'', ''[[Cinderella (2015 Disney film)|Cinderella]]'', and ''[[The Jungle Book (2016 film)|The Jungle Book]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chitwood|first1=Adam|title=Rumor: Could Bill Condon Direct Disney's Live-Action BEAUTY AND THE BEAST?|url=https://collider.com/beauty-and-the-beast-bill-condon/|accessdate=May 20, 2015|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=April 11, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150524013704/http://collider.com/beauty-and-the-beast-bill-condon/|archivedate=May 24, 2015}}</ref> Two months later, [[Bill Condon]] signed on to direct the film from a script by [[Evan Spiliotopoulos]].<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title=Bill Condon to Direct Live-Action 'Beauty and the Beast' Film for Disney|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/bill-condon-beauty-and-the-beast-disney-1201151834/|accessdate=January 27, 2015|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 4, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150206212052/http://variety.com/2014/film/news/bill-condon-beauty-and-the-beast-disney-1201151834/|archivedate=February 6, 2015}}</ref> Later in September of that same year, [[Stephen Chbosky]] (who directed [[Emma Watson]] in ''[[The Perks of Being a Wallflower (film)|The Perks of Being a Wallflower]]'') was hired to re-write the script.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Sperling |first=Nicole |url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/09/29/perks-of-being-a-wallflower-stephen-chbosky-beauty-and-the-beast/ |title='Perks of Being a Wallflower' author will adapt 'Beauty and the Beast' |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 29, 2014 |accessdate=September 30, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141001025146/http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/09/29/perks-of-being-a-wallflower-stephen-chbosky-beauty-and-the-beast/ |archivedate=October 1, 2014  }}</ref>\n\nBefore Condon was hired to direct the film, Disney approached him with a proposal to remake the film in a more radical way as [[Universal Studios]] had remade ''[[Snow White and the Huntsman]]'' (2012). Condon later explained that \"after ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]'' opened, the studio saw that there was this big international audience for an old-school-musical approach. But initially, they said, 'We're interested in a musical to a degree, but only half full of songs.' My interest was taking that film and doing it in this new medium\u2014live-action\u2014as a full-on musical movie. So I backed out for a minute, and they came back and said, 'No, no, no, we get it, let's pursue it that way.{{'\"}}<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kilday|first1=Gregg|title='Beauty and the Beast' Director on How 'La La Land' Is Bringing Musicals Back|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-director-bill-condon-bringing-musicals-back-981418|accessdate=April 3, 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=March 2, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303020143/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-director-bill-condon-bringing-musicals-back-981418|archivedate=March 3, 2017}}</ref> Walt Disney Pictures President of Production [[Sean Bailey]] credited [[Walt Disney Studios (division)|Walt Disney Studios]] chairman [[Alan F. Horn]] with the decision to make the film as a musical: \"We worked on this for five or six years, and for 18 months to two years, ''Beauty'' was a serious dramatic project, and the scripts were written to reflect that. It wasn't a musical at that time. But we just couldn't get it to click and it was Alan Horn who championed the idea of owning the Disney of it all. We realized there was a [[competitive advantage]] in the songs. What is wrong with making adults feel like kids again?\"<ref name=\"deadline.com\">{{cite news|last1=Fleming, Jr.|first1=Mike|title=Sean Bailey on How Disney's Live-Action Division Found Its 'Beauty and the Beast' Mojo|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-sean-bailey-disney-emma-watson-1202047710/|accessdate=April 3, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|publisher=Penske Business Media|date=March 21, 2017|location=Los Angeles|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910100558/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-sean-bailey-disney-emma-watson-1202047710/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> The film's ending originally featured Gaston being cursed by the Enchantress, though the idea was scrapped.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1746719/the-live-action-beauty-and-the-beast-almost-got-a-sequel-heres-what-it-would-have-been-about|title=The Live Action Beauty and the Beast Almost Got a Sequel, Here's What It Would Have Been About|website=Cinema Blend|first=Nick|last=Evans|access-date=April 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190428043712/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1746719/the-live-action-beauty-and-the-beast-almost-got-a-sequel-heres-what-it-would-have-been-about|archive-date=April 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn January 2015, it was announced that [[Emma Watson]] had been cast as [[Belle (Beauty and the Beast)|Belle]], the female lead.<ref name=WatsonCast>{{cit news|last1=Hayden|first1=Erik|title=Emma Watson Cast in Disney's Live-Action 'Beauty and the Beast'|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/emma-watson-cast-disneys-live-767095|accessdate=January 27, 2015|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 26, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103025144/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/emma-watson-cast-disneys-live-767095|archivedate=January 3, 2017}}</ref> She was the first and only choice of Walt Disney Studios chairman [[Alan F. Horn]], as he had previously run [[Warner Bros.]], which released the eight [[Harry Potter (film series)|''Harry Potter'' films]] that starred Watson as [[Hermione Granger]].<ref name=\"deadline.com\"/> Two months later, [[Luke Evans]] and [[Dan Stevens]] were revealed to be in talks to play Gaston and the Beast respectively,<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title=Luke Evans to Play Gaston in Disney's 'Beauty and the Beast' (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/luke-evans-to-play-gaston-in-disneys-beauty-and-the-beast-1201446186/|accessdate=March 9, 2015|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 4, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306171945/http://variety.com/2015/film/news/luke-evans-to-play-gaston-in-disneys-beauty-and-the-beast-1201446186/|archivedate=March 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|title=Disney's 'Beauty and the Beast' Casting Dan Stevens as the Beast (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-beauty-beast-casts-dan-779323|accessdate=March 9, 2015|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 4, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150305215127/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-beauty-beast-casts-dan-779323|archivedate=March 5, 2015}}</ref> and Watson confirmed their casting the following day via [[Twitter]].<ref name=StevensCast>{{cite tweet|author=Emma Watson|author-link=Emma Watson|user=EmWatson|title=Could not be more happy that this man will be Beast!!! Welcome aboard @thatdanstevens #beautyandthebeast pic.twitter.com/F1ghG3pvcU|number=573425651149094912|date=March 5, 2015|accessdate=March 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=EvansCast>{{cite tweet|author=Emma Watson|author-link=Emma Watson|user=EmWatson|title=Bonjour Gaston! \u2764\ufe0f Welcome! #BeautyAndTheBeast pic.twitter.com/oerhe1ilGs|number=573430507633000448|date=March 5, 2015|accessdate=March 9, 2015}}</ref> The rest of the principal cast, including [[Josh Gad]], [[Emma Thompson]], [[Kevin Kline]], [[Audra McDonald]], [[Ian McKellen]], [[Gugu Mbatha-Raw]], [[Ewan McGregor]], and [[Stanley Tucci]] were announced between March and April to play LeFou, Mrs. Potts, Maurice, Madame de Garderobe, Cogsworth, Plumette, Lumi\u00e8re, and Cadenza, respectively.<ref name=\"ReleaseThompsonKline\" /><ref name=GadCast>{{cite news|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|title=Josh Gad Joining Disney's Live-Action 'Beauty and the Beast' (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/josh-gad-joining-disneys-live-781061|accessdate=March 15, 2015|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 13, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150315004459/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/josh-gad-joining-disneys-live-781061|archivedate=March 15, 2015}}</ref><ref name=McGregorCast>{{cite news|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|title=Ewan McGregor to Play Lumiere in 'Beauty and the Beast' (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/ewan-mcgregor-play-lumiere-beauty-790480|accessdate=May 19, 2015|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 21, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150421191739/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/ewan-mcgregor-play-lumiere-beauty-790480|archivedate=April 21, 2015}}</ref><ref name=TucciCast>{{cite magazine|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/stanley-tucci-beauty-and-the-beast-casting-1201476986/|title=Stanley Tucci Rounds Out Cast of 'Beauty and the Beast' (EXCLUSIVE)|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 21, 2015|accessdate=May 19, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150517143040/http://variety.com/2015/film/news/stanley-tucci-beauty-and-the-beast-casting-1201476986/|archivedate=May 17, 2015}}</ref><ref name=McDonaldCast>{{cite news|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|title=Audra McDonald Joining Disney's Live-Action 'Beauty and the Beast' (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/audra-mcdonald-joining-disneys-live-784159|accessdate=April 16, 2015|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 27, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150520081714/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/audra-mcdonald-joining-disneys-live-784159|archivedate=May 20, 2015}}</ref><ref name=RawCast>{{cite magazine|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title='Beyond the Lights' Star Gugu Mbatha-Raw Joins 'Beauty and the Beast' (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-gugu-mbatha-raw-plumette-1201470581/|accessdate=April 14, 2015|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 13, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414180211/http://variety.com/2015/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-gugu-mbatha-raw-plumette-1201470581/|archivedate=April 14, 2015}}</ref><ref name=McKellenCast>{{cite magazine|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title=Ian McKellen to Play Cogsworth in Disney's 'Beauty and the Beast' (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/beauty-beast-ian-mckellen-cogsworth-1201464763/|accessdate=April 11, 2015|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 10, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411192321/http://variety.com/2015/film/news/beauty-beast-ian-mckellen-cogsworth-1201464763/|archivedate=April 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://decoy.tvpassport.com/q_a/q-january-i-read-emma-watson-was-star-disneys-live-action-beauty-and-beast-film-and-production-w?subid=national-00001|title=Q & A|last=Thomlison|first=Adam|publisher=TV Media|accessdate=August 3, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151003043039/http://decoy.tvpassport.com/q_a/q-january-i-read-emma-watson-was-star-disneys-live-action-beauty-and-beast-film-and-production-w?subid=national-00001|archivedate=October 3, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Susan Egan]], who originated the role of Belle on Broadway, commented on the casting of Watson as \"perfect\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Original-Broadway-Belle-Susan-Egan-Comments-on-Emma-Watson-in-BEAUTY-AND-THE-BEAST-20150126|title=Original Broadway 'Belle' Susan Egan Comments on Emma Watson in BEAUTY AND THE BEAST|work=Broadway World|date=January 26, 2015|accessdate=August 11, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910101739/https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Original-Broadway-Belle-Susan-Egan-Comments-on-Emma-Watson-in-BEAUTY-AND-THE-BEAST-20150126|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> [[Paige O'Hara]], who voiced Belle in the original animated film and its sequels, offered to help Watson with her singing lessons.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://watsonuncensored.blogspot.com/2015/02/paige-ohara-wants-to-teach-emma-watson.html|title=Paige O'Hara wants to teach Emma Watson|work=Emma Watson Updates|date=February 4, 2015|accessdate=August 11, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304233033/http://watsonuncensored.blogspot.com/2015/02/paige-ohara-wants-to-teach-emma-watson.html|archivedate=March 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', Watson was reportedly paid $3&nbsp;million upfront, together with an agreement that her final take-home pay could rise as high as $15&nbsp;million if the film generated gross box office income similar to ''[[Maleficent (film)|Maleficent]]''{{'}}s $759&nbsp;million worldwide gross.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/how-emma-watson-is-getting-paid-beauty-beast-986316|title=Emma Watson and What Disney Pays Its Modern Princesses|author=Tatiana Siegel|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170426020601/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/how-emma-watson-is-getting-paid-beauty-beast-986316|archivedate=April 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began on May 18, 2015, at [[Shepperton Studios]] in [[Surrey]], England.<ref name=\"ReleaseThompsonKline\"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Foutch|first1=Haleigh|title=Todd Lieberman Offers Updates on Allegiant and Disney's Beauty and the Beast|url=https://collider.com/allegiant-movie-ending-beauty-and-the-beast-todd-lieberman/|accessdate=May 19, 2015|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=March 7, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910104248/http://collider.com/allegiant-movie-ending-beauty-and-the-beast-todd-lieberman/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=On the Set for 5/18/15: Emma Watson Starts 'Beauty and the Beast', Oliver Stone Wraps 'Snowden', Melissa Mccarthy Finishes 'Michelle Darnell' & More|url=http://www.ssninsider.com/on-the-set-for-51815-emma-watson-starts-beauty-and-the-beast-oliver-stone-wraps-snowden-melissa-mccarthy-finishes-michelle-darnell-more/|accessdate=May 18, 2015|publisher=SSN Insider|date=May 18, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150520081716/http://www.ssninsider.com/on-the-set-for-51815-emma-watson-starts-beauty-and-the-beast-oliver-stone-wraps-snowden-melissa-mccarthy-finishes-michelle-darnell-more/|archivedate=May 20, 2015}}</ref> Filming with the principal actors concluded on August 21.<ref>{{cite web|last=Trumbore|first=Dave|title=Emma Watson Wraps 'Beauty and the Beast' on 'Harry Potter' Anniversary|url=https://collider.com/emma-watson-wraps-beauty-and-the-beast-on-harry-potter-anniversary/|accessdate=August 23, 2015|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=August 23, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20151006231053/http://collider.com/emma-watson-wraps-beauty-and-the-beast-on-harry-potter-anniversary/|archivedate=October 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Twitter Watch: Emma Watson & Luke Evans Wrap Filming on BEAUTY AND THE BEAST|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Twitter-Watch-Emma-Watson-Luke-Evans-Wrap-Filming-on-BEAUTY-AND-THE-BEAST-20150824|accessdate=August 27, 2015|website=Broadway World|date=August 24, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910105256/https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Twitter-Watch-Emma-Watson-Luke-Evans-Wrap-Filming-on-BEAUTY-AND-THE-BEAST-20150824|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> Six days later, co-producer Jack Morrissey confirmed that production had officially wrapped.<ref>{{cite web|title=Disney's Live Action BEAUTY AND THE BEAST Officially Wraps Production!|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Disneys-Live-Action-BEAUTY-AND-THE-BEAST-Officially-Wraps-Production-20150827|accessdate=August 27, 2015|website=Broadway World|date=August 27, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910105349/https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Disneys-Live-Action-BEAUTY-AND-THE-BEAST-Officially-Wraps-Production-20150827|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe Beast was portrayed with a \"more traditional motion capture puppeteering for the body and the physical orientation\", where actor Dan Stevens was \"in a forty-pound gray suit on stilts for much of the film\". The facial capture for the Beast was done separately in order to \"communicate the subtleties of the human face\" and \"[capture the] thought that occurs to him\" which gets \"through [to] the eyes, which are the last human element in the Beast.\" The castle servants who are transformed into household objects were created with [[computer animation|CGI animation]].<ref name=\"Penske Business Media\"/>\n\nBefore the release of the film, Bill Condon refilmed one certain sequence in the \"Days of the Sun\" number, due to confusion among test audiences caused by actress Harriet Jones, who looked similar to [[Hattie Morahan]], who portrayed Agathe. In the original version of the scene, it was Jones's character, the Prince's mother, who sings the first verse of the song, with Rudi Goodman playing the young Prince and [[Henry Garrett (actor)|Henry Garrett]] playing his father; but in the reshot version of the scene, the singing part is given to the Prince (now played by Adam Mitchell). The King was also recast to Tom Turner, although Harriet Jones was still the Queen, albeit with dark hair. Both Goodman and Garrett's names were mistakenly featured in the original theatrical release's credits, but was later corrected in home releases.<ref name=\"OriginalDaysInTheSun\"/>\n\n===Music===\n{{main|Beauty and the Beast (2017 soundtrack)}}\n\nWhen released in 1991, ''[[Beauty and the Beast (1991 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' marked a turning point for [[Walt Disney Pictures]] by appealing to millions of fans with its Oscar-winning musical score by lyricist [[Howard Ashman]] and composer [[Alan Menken]]. In [[Bill Condon]]'s opinion, that original score was the key reason he agreed to direct a live-action version of the movie. \"That score had more to reveal\", he says, \"You look at the songs and there's not a clunker in the group. In fact, [[Frank Rich]] described it as the best Broadway musical of 1991. The animated version was already darker and more modern than the previous Disney fairy-tales. Take that vision, put it into a new medium, make it a radical reinvention, something not just for the stage because it's not just being literal, now other elements come into play. It's not just having real actors do it\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.filmjournal.com/features/tale-old-time-bill-condon-livens-disneys-beauty-and-the-beast |title=Tale as Old as Time: Bill Condon livens up Disney's 'Beauty and the Beast' &#124; Film Journal International |publisher=Filmjournal.com |accessdate=March 8, 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910110809/http://www.filmjournal.com/features/tale-old-time-bill-condon-livens-disneys-beauty-and-the-beast |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref>\n\nCondon initially prepared on only drawing inspiration from the original film, but he also planned to include most of the songs composed by Menken, Ashman and [[Tim Rice]] from the [[Beauty and the Beast (musical)|Broadway musical]], with the intention of making the film as a \"straight-forward, live-action, large-budget movie musical\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Tapley|first=Kristopher|url=http://www.hitfix.com/in-contention/twilight-director-bill-condon-to-translate-disneys-beauty-and-the-beat-to-live-action#XlmGEuY4YfavH3C3.99|title='Twilight' director Bill Condon will translate Disney's 'Beauty and the Beast' to live action (UPDATED)|work=[[HitFix]]|date=June 4, 2014|accessdate=June 5, 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20140605035738/http://www.hitfix.com/in-contention/twilight-director-bill-condon-to-translate-disneys-beauty-and-the-beat-to-live-action%23XlmGEuY4YfavH3C3.99|archivedate=June 5, 2014}}</ref> Menken returned to score the film's music, which features songs from the original film by him and Ashman, plus new material written by Menken and Rice.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=Disney's Live-Action 'Beauty and the Beast' Set for March 17, 2017|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-release-date-disney-live-action-2017-1201453646/|accessdate=May 28, 2015|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 16, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150517011233/http://variety.com/2015/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-release-date-disney-live-action-2017-1201453646/|archivedate=May 17, 2015}}</ref> Menken said the film would not include songs that were written for the Broadway musical and, instead, created four new songs.<ref>{{cite web|last=Robbins|first=Caryn|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Alan-Menken-Confirms-3-New-Songs-for-BEAUTY-AND-THE-BEAST-Film-Broadway-Tunes-Will-Not-Be-Included-20150605|title=Alan Menken Confirms 3 New Songs for BEAUTY AND THE BEAST Film; Broadway Tunes Will Not Be Included|website=Broadway World|date=June 5, 2015|accessdate=June 5, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910111047/https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Alan-Menken-Confirms-3-New-Songs-for-BEAUTY-AND-THE-BEAST-Film-Broadway-Tunes-Will-Not-Be-Included-20150605|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> However, an instrumental version of the song \"Home\", which was written for the musical, is used during the scene where Belle first enters her room in the castle.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Ashley|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/beauty-beast-new-songs-composer-alan-menken-lost-lyrics-gay-character-985602|title='Beauty and the Beast' Composer Alan Menken on Rediscovering Lost Lyrics and Why He's \"Shutting Up\" About That Gay Character|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 14, 2017|accessdate=March 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910111145/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/beauty-beast-new-songs-composer-alan-menken-lost-lyrics-gay-character-985602|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn January 19, 2017, both Disney and [[C\u00e9line Dion]] \u2014 singer of the original 1991 \"[[Beauty and the Beast (Disney song)|Beauty and the Beast]]\" duet song, with singer [[Peabo Bryson]] \u2014 confirmed that Dion would be performing one of the new original songs \"[[How Does a Moment Last Forever]]\" to play over the end titles.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://people.com/music/celine-dion-beauty-and-the-beast-soundtrack-song/ |title=C\u00e9line Dion Set to Perform New Song for Live-Action Beauty and the Beast Soundtrack |work=People |department=Music |date=January 19, 2017 |accessdate=January 26, 2017 |author=Tracy, Brianne |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910111242/http://people.com/music/celine-dion-beauty-and-the-beast-soundtrack-song/ |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref> She originally had doubts about whether or not to record the song due to the recent death of her husband and manager [[Ren\u00e9 Ang\u00e9lil]], who had previously helped her secure the 1991 pop duet. While ultimately accepting the opportunity, she said: \"[The] first Beauty and the Beast decision was made with my husband. Now I'm making decisions on my own. It's a little bit harder. I couldn't say yes right away, because I felt like I was kind of cheating in a way\". She eventually felt compelled to record the song because of the impact ''Beauty and the Beast'' has had on her career. According to Dion, \"I was at the beginning of my career, it put me on the map, it put me where I am today\". Also, [[Josh Groban]] was announced to be performing the new original song \"[[Evermore (Beauty and the Beast song)|Evermore]]\" six days later.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.instagram.com/p/BPdWUimAEhA/|title = I am thrilled to announce that I'll be performing an all-new original song, \"How Does A Moment Last Forever,\" for Disney's live-action Beauty and the Beast. Being a part of the original film was such a magical experience in my life, and I'm truly honored to be a part of this film again. // Je suis ravie de vous annoncer que je chanterai la nouvelle chanson th\u00e8me du film ''La Belle et la B\u00eate'', \"How Does A Moment Last Forever\". Avoir fait partie du film original de Disney a \u00e9t\u00e9 une exp\u00e9rience magique dans ma vie et je suis encore plus honor\u00e9e de r\u00e9p\u00e9ter cette exp\u00e9rience. \u2013 C\u00e9line|work = Instagram|date = January 19, 2017|accessdate = January 20, 2017|last = Dion|first = C\u00e9line|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170316043802/https://www.instagram.com/p/BPdWUimAEhA/|archivedate = March 16, 2017|df = mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://people.com/music/celine-dion-beauty-and-the-beast-soundtrack-song/|title = C\u00e9line Dion Set to Perform New Song for Live-Action Beauty and the Beast Soundtrack|work = People|date = January 19, 2017|accessdate = January 20, 2017|last = Tracey|first = Brianne|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://archive.today/20170910111242/http://people.com/music/celine-dion-beauty-and-the-beast-soundtrack-song/|archivedate = September 10, 2017|df = mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://finance.yahoo.com/news/celine-dion-perform-original-song-201000316.html |title=C\u00e9line Dion To Perform Original Song \"How Does A Moment Last Forever\" For Disney's \"Beauty and the Beast\" |date=January 19, 2017 |accessdate=January 19, 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202055805/http://finance.yahoo.com/news/celine-dion-perform-original-song-201000316.html |archivedate=February 2, 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Oliver |last=Gettell |url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/01/26/josh-groban-beauty-and-the-beast-song-evermore/ |title=Beauty and the Beast: Josh Groban records new song Evermore |publisher=Ew.com |date=January 26, 2017 |accessdate=March 2, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170225112113/http://ew.com/movies/2017/01/26/josh-groban-beauty-and-the-beast-song-evermore/ |archivedate=February 25, 2017  }}</ref>\n\nThe 2017 film features a remake of the 1991 original song recorded as a duet by [[Ariana Grande]] and [[John Legend]].<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.instagram.com/p/BPGesF2lNVE/|title = Ariana Grande on Instagram: \"\ud83e\udd40.\"|work = Instagram|date = January 10, 2017|accessdate = January 11, 2017|last = Grande|first = Ariana|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180104060640/https://www.instagram.com/p/BPGesF2lNVE/|archivedate = January 4, 2018|df = mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.eonline.com/news/821374/it-looks-like-ariana-grande-and-john-legend-are-teaming-up-for-a-beauty-and-the-beast-duetl|title = It Looks Like Ariana Grande and John Legend Are Teaming Up for a Beauty and the Beast Duet|work = E!|date = January 10, 2017|accessdate = January 11, 2017|last = Nessif|first = Bruna|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170113012445/http://www.eonline.com/news/821374/it-looks-like-ariana-grande-and-john-legend-are-teaming-up-for-a-beauty-and-the-beast-duetl|archivedate = January 13, 2017|df = mdy-all}}</ref> Grande and Legend's updated version of the title song is faithful to the original, Grammy-winning duet, performed by C\u00e9line Dion and Peabo Bryson for the 1991 Disney film.<ref>{{cite web |last=Reed |first=Ryan |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-ariana-grande-john-legend-cover-beauty-and-the-beast-theme-w470582 |title=Watch Ariana Grande, John Legend Cover 'Beauty and the Beast' Theme |work=Rolling Stone |accessdate=March 8, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910111732/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-ariana-grande-john-legend-cover-beauty-and-the-beast-theme-w470582 |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref> \nDisney debuted the music video for Ariana Grande and John Legend's interpretation of the title song on [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] television network on March 5, 2017, and it has since been viewed over 100 million views on the [[Vevo]] video-hosting service.<ref name=\"variety1\"/>\n\n[[Emma Thompson]] also performed a rendition of the title song, which was performed by [[Angela Lansbury]] in the original 1991 animated film.<ref name=\"variety1\">{{cite magazine |author=Maane Khatchatourian |url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/ariana-grande-john-legend-beauty-and-the-beast-music-video-1202002624/ |title=Beauty and the Beast Music Video: Ariana Grande John Legend Sing Theme |magazine=Variety |accessdate=March 8, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307142007/http://variety.com/2017/music/news/ariana-grande-john-legend-beauty-and-the-beast-music-video-1202002624/ |archivedate=March 7, 2017  }}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nOn March 16, 2015, Disney announced the film would be released in 3D on March 17, 2017.<ref name=\"ReleaseThompsonKline\">{{cite news|last1=Ford|first1=Rebecca|title=Disney's Live-Action 'Beauty and the Beast' Gets Release Date|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disneys-live-action-beauty-beast-781683|accessdate=March 16, 2015|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 16, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170107180606/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disneys-live-action-beauty-beast-781683|archivedate=January 7, 2017}}</ref> The first official presentation of the film took place at Disney's three-day [[D23 (Disney)|D23 Expo]] in August 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Couch|first1=Aaron|last2=Kit|first2=Borys|title=Disney Shows off 'Pirates 5,' 'Beauty and the Beast' at D23|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disney-shows-pirates-5-beauty-815626|accessdate=August 15, 2015|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=August 16, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150917063340/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disney-shows-pirates-5-beauty-815626|archivedate=September 17, 2015}}</ref>\n\n''Beauty and the Beast'' had its world premiere at [[Spencer House, London|Spencer House]] in London on February 23, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.scmp.com/culture/film-tv/article/2073782/emma-watson-champions-very-progressive-belle-beauty-and-beast-london |title=Archived copy |access-date=November 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110232408/https://www.scmp.com/culture/film-tv/article/2073782/emma-watson-champions-very-progressive-belle-beauty-and-beast-london |archive-date=November 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The US premiere was held at the [[El Capitan Theatre]] in Hollywood on March 2, 2017. The stream was broadcast onto [[YouTube]].\n\nA sing along version of the film released in over 1,200 US theaters nationwide on April 7, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insidethemagic.net/2017/04/beauty-beast-sing-along-hit-theaters-friday/|title=\"Beauty and the Beast Sing Along\" to hit theaters this Friday|author=JeniLynn Knopp|publisher=Inside the Magic|date=April 3, 2017|accessdate=April 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910160852/http://www.insidethemagic.net/2017/04/beauty-beast-sing-along-hit-theaters-friday/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> The United Kingdom received the same version on April 21, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cineworld.co.uk/films/beauty-and-the-beast-sing-a-long|title=Beauty and the Beast Sing-A-Long {{!}} Book tickets at Cineworld Cinemas|website=www.cineworld.co.uk|access-date=January 19, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120065809/https://www.cineworld.co.uk/films/beauty-and-the-beast-sing-a-long|archive-date=January 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe film was re-released in New York and Los Angeles for a one-week engagement starting December 1, 2017. The movie was an awards push as the [[2017\u201318 film awards season|2017\u201318 awards season]] heated up.<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/11/27/beauty-and-the-beast-returning-theaters/|title=Beauty and Beast returns to theaters|last=Collis|first=Clark|journal=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=November 27, 2017|accessdate=December 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171202101320/http://ew.com/movies/2017/11/27/beauty-and-the-beast-returning-theaters/|archive-date=December 2, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nDisney spent around $140&nbsp;million to market the film worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.nytimes.com/2017/03/08/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-disneys-300-million-gamble.html|title='Beauty and the Beast': Disney's $300 Million Gamble|author=Brooks Barnes|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=March 8, 2017|accessdate=March 8, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309061743/https://mobile.nytimes.com/2017/03/08/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-disneys-300-million-gamble.html|archivedate=March 9, 2017}}</ref> Following an announcement on May 22, 2016,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gallagher|first1=Simon|title=Disney's Live Action Beauty & The Beast Trailer Debuts Tomorrow|url=http://whatculture.com/film/disneys-live-action-beauty-the-beast-trailer-debuts-tomorrow|website=WhatCulture.com|accessdate=May 22, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610145001/http://whatculture.com/film/disneys-live-action-beauty-the-beast-trailer-debuts-tomorrow|archivedate=June 10, 2016}}</ref> Disney premiered the first official teaser trailer on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' the next day.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Collis|first1=Clark|title=Beauty and the Beast trailer: Disney's live-action remake debuts first teaser|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/23/beauty-beast-trailer-emma-watson|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=May 23, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20160627062604/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/23/beauty-beast-trailer-emma-watson|archivedate=June 27, 2016}}</ref> In its first 24 hours, the teaser trailer reached 91.8&nbsp;million views, which was the largest number ever seen for a trailer in that amount of time.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gettell|first1=Oliver|title=Beauty and the Beast teaser outpaces Star Wars, Marvel in first day|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/24/beauty-beast-teaser-tops-star-wars-marvel|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=May 25, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20160627062616/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/05/24/beauty-beast-teaser-tops-star-wars-marvel|archivedate=June 27, 2016}}</ref> This record has since been broken by ''[[Thor: Ragnarok]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/thor-ragnarok-trailer-is-marvel-disneys-watched-ever-24-hours-992978 |title='Thor: Ragnarok' Trailer Is Marvel and Disney's Most Watched Ever in 24 Hours (Exclusive) |last=Kit |first=Borys |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=April 11, 2017 |accessdate=April 11, 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412013813/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/thor-ragnarok-trailer-is-marvel-disneys-watched-ever-24-hours-992978 |archivedate=April 12, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[It (2017 film)|It]]'', and ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]''.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Spangler |first=Todd |title='Avengers: Infinity War\u2019 Tops List of 2018 Most-Anticipated Movies, IMDb Data Reveals |url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/avengers-infinity-war-2018-most-anticipated-movies-imdb-1202645136/ |date=December 19, 2017 |access-date=January 19, 2018 |journal=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180101043425/https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/avengers-infinity-war-2018-most-anticipated-movies-imdb-1202645136/ |archive-date=January 1, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Drum |first=Nicole |title='Avengers: Infinity War' Is Most Anticipated Movie According to IMDb |url=https://comicbook.com/marvel/2017/12/19/avengers-infinity-war-most-anticipated-movie-imdb/ |date=December 19, 2017 |access-date=January 19, 2018 |journal=Comicbook |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120070630/http://comicbook.com/marvel/2017/12/19/avengers-infinity-war-most-anticipated-movie-imdb/ |archive-date=January 20, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The first official teaser poster was released on July 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Collis|first1=Clark|title=Beauty and the Beast debuts new teaser poster with flower power|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/07/07/beauty-and-the-beast-poster|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=July 7, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20160908033148/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/07/07/beauty-and-the-beast-poster|archivedate=September 8, 2016}}</ref> On November 2, 2016, ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' debuted the first official image on the cover of their magazine, along with nine new photos.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Collis|first1=Clark|title=This Week's Cover: Be our guest for an exclusive look at Disney's live-action Beauty and the Beast|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/02/beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-ew-cover|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=November 2, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20161113000729/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/02/beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-ew-cover|archivedate=November 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=EW Staff|title='Beauty and the Beast': See 9 Enchanting, Exclusive Photos|url=https://www.ew.com/gallery/beauty-and-the-beast-photos|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=November 2, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20161103173404/http://www.ew.com/gallery/beauty-and-the-beast-photos|archivedate=November 3, 2016}}</ref> One week later, Emma Watson and Disney debuted a new poster.<ref>{{cite web|author=Danielle Jackson|title=Emma Watson shares stunning new teaser poster for Beauty and the Beast|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/10/beauty-and-the-beast-teaser-poster-emma-watson|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=November 11, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20161113000714/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/10/beauty-and-the-beast-teaser-poster-emma-watson|archivedate=November 13, 2016}}</ref> On November 14, 2016, the first theatrical trailer was released, again on ''Good Morning America''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jessica Derschowitz|title=Beauty and the Beast debuts magical new trailer|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/14/beauty-and-the-beast-trailer-emma-watson-dan-stevens|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=November 14, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20161114183026/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/14/beauty-and-the-beast-trailer-emma-watson-dan-stevens|archivedate=November 14, 2016}}</ref> This reached 127.6&nbsp;million views in its first 24 hours, setting a new record for the most views in one day, beating ''[[Fifty Shades Darker (film)|Fifty Shades Darker]]'';<ref>{{cite web|author=Clark Collis|title=Beauty and the Beast trailer beats Fifty Shades, Star Wars for new record|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/15/beauty-and-the-beast-trailer-record|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=November 15, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115225040/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/11/15/beauty-and-the-beast-trailer-record|archivedate=November 15, 2016}}</ref> this record has since been broken by ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kofi Outlaw|title=Fate of the Furious Trailer Breaks Record for Most Views in 24 Hours|url=https://comicbook.com/popculturenow/2016/12/13/fate-furious-trailer-breaks-record-most-views/|work=ComicBook.com|accessdate=January 8, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910162913/http://comicbook.com/popculturenow/2016/12/13/fate-furious-trailer-breaks-record-most-views/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> A TV spot with Watson singing was shown during the [[74th Golden Globe Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Scott Mendelson|title=Watch Emma Watson Sing 'Belle' In Disney's 'Beauty and the Beast' TV Spot|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/01/08/watch-emma-watson-sing-belle-in-disneys-beauty-and-the-beast-tv-spot|work=Forbes.com|accessdate=January 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910222435/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/01/08/watch-emma-watson-sing-belle-in-disneys-beauty-and-the-beast-tv-spot/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> Disney released the final trailer on January 30, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|author=Clark Collis|title=Beauty and the Beast: Watch the final trailer|url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/01/30/beauty-and-the-beast-trailer/|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=January 31, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910165110/http://ew.com/movies/2017/01/30/beauty-and-the-beast-trailer/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''Beauty and the Beast'' was released on Blu-ray, DVD, and Digital HD on June 6, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thekingdominsider.com/disneys-beauty-beast-comes-blu-ray-digital-hd-dvd-june-6/|title=Disney's 'Beauty and the Beast' Comes to Blu-ray, Digital HD and DVD on June 6|last=Pratt|first=Thom|work=The Kingdom Insider|date=May 12, 2017|accessdate=May 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910165350/http://thekingdominsider.com/disneys-beauty-beast-comes-blu-ray-digital-hd-dvd-june-6/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> The film debuted at No. 1 on the NPD VideoScan overall disc sales chart, with all other titles in the top 20, collectively, selling only 40% as many units as ''Beauty and the Beast''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/beauty-and-the-beast-debuts-atop-disc-charts-1202466683/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Debuts Atop Disc Charts|last=Arnold|first=Thomas K.|work=Variety|date=June 14, 2017|accessdate=June 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170615024933/http://variety.com/2017/digital/news/beauty-and-the-beast-debuts-atop-disc-charts-1202466683/|archivedate=June 15, 2017}}</ref> The film regained the top spot on the national home video sales charts during its third week of release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/beauty-and-the-beast-regains-top-spot-on-disc-charts-1202482084/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Regains Top Spot on Disc Charts|last=Arnold|first=Thomas K.|work=Variety|date=June 28, 2017|accessdate=June 29, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170629062743/http://variety.com/2017/digital/news/beauty-and-the-beast-regains-top-spot-on-disc-charts-1202482084/|archivedate=June 29, 2017}}</ref> The film became available on [[Netflix]] on September 19, 2017. ''Beauty and the Beast'' was released on [[Ultra HD Blu-ray|4K Blu-Ray]] on March 10, 2020 along with the [[Beauty and the Beast (1991 film)|original animated film]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Beauty and the Beast 4K Blu-ray Release Date March 10, 2020|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Beauty-and-the-Beast-4K-Blu-ray/259303/|access-date=2020-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203144340/https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Beauty-and-the-Beast-4K-Blu-ray/259303/|archive-date=February 3, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n[[File:Emma Watson 2013.jpg|thumb|upright|Praised for her performance as Belle worldwide, ''Beauty and the Beast'' is [[Emma Watson]]'s highest-grossing film in the domestic side and second-highest-grossing film, behind only the final ''[[Harry Potter (film series)|Harry Potter]]'' film, ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/people/chart/?view=Actor&id=emmawatson.htm&sort=gross&order=DESC&p=.htm|title=Emma Watson|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=April 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413234655/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/people/chart/?view=Actor&id=emmawatson.htm&sort=gross&order=DESC&p=.htm|archivedate=April 13, 2017}}</ref>]]\n''Beauty and the Beast'' grossed $504&nbsp;million in the United States and Canada and $759.5&nbsp;million in other countries for a worldwide gross of $1.263&nbsp;billion.<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=beautyandthebeast2017.htm|title=''Beauty and the Beast'' (2017)|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=August 14, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815114547/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=beautyandthebeast2017.htm|archive-date=August 15, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> With a production budget of $254&nbsp;million, it is the most expensive musical ever made.<ref name=ForbesBudget>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/csylt/2018/06/08/the-255-million-spell-that-disney-cast-on-britain/|title=The $255 Million Spell That Disney Cast On Britain|author=Christian Sylt|magazine=[[Forbes]]|date=June 8, 2018|accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180815220733/https://www.forbes.com/sites/csylt/2018/06/08/the-255-million-spell-that-disney-cast-on-britain/|archive-date=August 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Anne Thompson\">{{cite news|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/03/420-disney-beauty-and-the-beast-bill-condon-emma-watson-musical-1201791591/|title='Beauty and the Beast': How Bill Condon Built Hollywood's Most Expensive Musical|author=Anne Thompson|work=[[IndieWire]]|date=March 14, 2017|accessdate=March 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801050232/http://www.indiewire.com/2017/03/420-disney-beauty-and-the-beast-bill-condon-emma-watson-musical-1201791591/|archivedate=August 1, 2017}}</ref> In just ten days, it became the highest-grossing live-action musical of all time, beating the nine-year-old record held by ''[[Mamma Mia! (film)|Mamma Mia!]]''. It also became the second-biggest musical ever overall at the time, behind Disney's ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]'' (2013).<ref name=\"MUSIC\"/> Worldwide, the film proved to be a global phenomenon, earning a total of $357&nbsp;million over its four-day opening weekend from 56 markets. Critics said the film was playing like superhero movies amongst women. It was the second-biggest March global opening, behind only ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'', the [[List of highest-grossing openings for films|thirteenth-biggest worldwide opening ever]] and the seventh-biggest for Disney.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/world/worldwideopenings.htm|title=WORLDWIDE OPENINGS|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110623165250/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/world/worldwideopenings.htm|archivedate=June 23, 2011}}</ref> This includes $21&nbsp;million from IMAX plays on 1,026 screens, a new record for an IMAX PG title.<ref name=\"WWW\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-logan-kong-skull-island-international-box-office-1202046567/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Enchants With $350M Global Bow; $180M Offshore \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910174838/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-logan-kong-skull-island-international-box-office-1202046567/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> It surpassed the entire lifetime total of the original film in just six days.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-first-tuesday-international-global-box-office-1202048516/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Makes Room For $222M Offshore, $429M WW on Tuesday|author=Nancy Tartaglione|publisher=March 22, 2017|accessdate=March 23, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910170725/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-first-tuesday-international-global-box-office-1202048516/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-crossing-500-million-worldwide-box-office-1202050957/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Crosses $500M at Worldwide Box Office|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910170851/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-crossing-500-million-worldwide-box-office-1202050957/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\n''Beauty and the Beast'' was the 300th digitally remastered release in IMAX company's history, which began with the re-release of ''[[Apollo 13 (film)|Apollo 13]]'' in 2002. Its robust global debut helped push the company past $6&nbsp;billion for the first time,<ref name=\"DOM\"/> and led to analysts believing that the film had a shot of passing $1&nbsp;billion worldwide from theatrical earnings.<ref name=\"NYT\">{{cite news|url=https://mobile.nytimes.com/2017/03/19/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-clobbers-record-with-170-million-opening.html|title='Beauty and the Beast' Clobbers Record With $170 Million Opening|author=Brooks Barnes|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320000640/https://mobile.nytimes.com/2017/03/19/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-clobbers-record-with-170-million-opening.html|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2017/03/17/beauty-and-the-beast-could-be-disneys-first-1-billion-film-of-2017.html|title='Beauty and the Beast' could be Disney's first $1&nbsp;billion film of 2017|author=Sarah Whitten|publisher=[[CNBC]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170319195036/http://www.cnbc.com/2017/03/17/beauty-and-the-beast-could-be-disneys-first-1-billion-film-of-2017.html|archivedate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beasts-secret-success-female-power-comfort-987258|title='Beauty and the Beast's' Secret to Success: Female Power and Comfort|author=Pamela McClintock|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320193622/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beasts-secret-success-female-power-comfort-987258|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.in/beauty-and-the-beast-could-make-1-5-billion-at-the-box-office-and-it-has-big-implications-for-disneys-future/articleshow/57757803.cms|title='Beauty and the Beast' could make $1.5&nbsp;billion at the box office, and it has big implications for Disney's future|author=Nathan McAlonemar|website=[[Business Insider]]|date=March 21, 2017|accessdate=March 23, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323234624/http://www.businessinsider.in/beauty-and-the-beast-could-make-1-5-billion-at-the-box-office-and-it-has-big-implications-for-disneys-future/articleshow/57757803.cms|archivedate=March 23, 2017}}</ref> On April 12, it passed the $1&nbsp;billion threshold, becoming the first film of 2017, the fourteenth Disney film, and the twenty-ninth film overall to pass the mark. It became the first film since ''[[Rogue One|Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]'' (also a Disney property) in December 2016 to make over a billion dollars, and did so on its 29th day of release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-beauty-beast-waltzing-past-1b-globally-993210|title=Box-Office Milestone: 'Beauty and the Beast' Waltzing Past $1B Globally|author=Pamela McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412204957/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-beauty-beast-waltzing-past-1b-globally-993210|archivedate=April 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-worldwide-box-office-3-1202029168/|title='Beauty and the Beast' to Cross $1 Billion at Worldwide Box Office|author=Dave McNarry|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413072314/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-worldwide-box-office-3-1202029168/|archivedate=April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Tot\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/beauty-and-the-beast-crosses-1-billion-worldwide-box-office-1202069325/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Roars Past $1B at Worldwide Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910175927/http://deadline.com/2017/04/beauty-and-the-beast-crosses-1-billion-worldwide-box-office-1202069325/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> It is currently the second-highest-grossing film of 2017 (behind ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]''),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2017&p=.htm|title=2017 WORLDWIDE GROSSES|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=April 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412025645/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2017&p=.htm|archivedate=April 12, 2017}}</ref> the highest-grossing March release,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/month/?mo=03&p=.htm|title=TOP OPENING WEEKENDS BY MONTH \u2013 MARCH|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=April 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316054849/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/month/?mo=03&p=.htm|archivedate=March 16, 2015}}</ref> the highest-grossing remake of all time,<ref name=\"SC\">{{cite news|url=http://m.screendaily.com/5116890.article|title=How well do Hollywood remakes fare at the box office?|author=Tom Grater|work=[[Screen Daily]]|date=April 22, 2017|accessdate=April 23, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170423063848/http://m.screendaily.com/5116890.article|archivedate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> and the sixth-biggest Disney film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/world/|title=WORLDWIDE GROSSES|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=May 21, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010716094602/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/world/|archivedate=July 16, 2001}}</ref> Even after inflation adjusted, it is still ahead of the $425&nbsp;million gross ($760&nbsp;million in 2017 dollars) of the original film.<ref name=\"SC\"/> ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' calculated the net profit of the film to be $414.7&nbsp;million, when factoring together all expenses and revenues, making it the second-most profitable release of 2017.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-profits-1202351594/|title=No. 2 'Beauty and the Beast' Box Office Profits \u2013 2017 Most Valuable Blockbuster Tournament|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 27, 2018|accessdate=March 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180328010153/http://deadline.com/2018/03/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-profits-1202351594/|archive-date=March 28, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====United States and Canada====\nIn the United States and Canada, ''Beauty and the Beast'' topped [[Fandango (company)|Fandango]]'s pre-sales and became the fastest-selling family film in the company's history, topping the studio's own animated film ''[[Finding Dory]]'' released the previous year. Early tracking had the film grossing around $100&nbsp;million in its opening weekend, with some publications predicting it could reach $130&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"proj1\">{{cite web|title='Beauty and the Beast' Roars on to Tracking, Looking to Shake Up March Records \u2013 Box Office Projection|url=https://deadline.com/2017/02/beauty-and-the-beast-big-march-box-office-opening-1201930478/|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=February 23, 2017|accessdate=March 4, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910171212/http://deadline.com/2017/02/beauty-and-the-beast-big-march-box-office-opening-1201930478/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-sets-new-record-advance-ticket-sales-986046|title='Beauty and the Beast' Sets New Record for Advance Ticket Sales|author=Pamela McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 14, 2017|accessdate=March 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910171334/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-sets-new-record-advance-ticket-sales-986046|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-prepares-break-box-office-records-986613|title=Box-Office Preview: Will 'Beauty and the Beast' Waltz to New Records?|author=Pamela McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 16, 2017|accessdate=March 16, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910171615/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-prepares-break-box-office-records-986613|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> By the time the film's release was 10 days away, analysts raised projections to as high as $150&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beasts-box-office-presales-beating-captain-america-civil-war-finding-dory-1202038233/|title=Proof That 'Beauty and the Beast' Will Tear Up March B.O. Records: Pre-Sales Are Through The Roof|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 6, 2017|accessdate=March 7, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910171801/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beasts-box-office-presales-beating-captain-america-civil-war-finding-dory-1202038233/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-beauty-and-the-beast-20170313-story.html|title=Why 'Beauty and the Beast' will be the biggest box-office hit of the year so far|author=Ryan Faughnder|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=March 15, 2017|accessdate=March 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910172331/http://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-beauty-and-the-beast-20170313-story.html|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> It earned $16.3&nbsp;million from Thursday previews night, marking the biggest of 2017 (breaking ''[[Logan (film)|Logan]]''{{'}}s record), the biggest ever for a Disney live-action film (breaking ''[[Maleficent (film)|Maleficent]]''{{'}}s record), the second-biggest ever for both a G- or PG-rated film (behind the sixth ''Harry Potter'' film ''[[Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince (film)|Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince]]'' which also starred Watson), and the third-biggest ever in the month of March (behind ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'' and ''[[The Hunger Games (film)|The Hunger Games]]'').<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movieweb.com/beauty-beast-movie-2017-disney-thursday-box-office/|title=Beauty and the Beast Roars Loudly with $16.3M at Thursday Box Office|author=Brian Gallagher|publisher=Movie Web|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317225728/http://movieweb.com/beauty-beast-movie-2017-disney-thursday-box-office/|archivedate=March 17, 2017}}</ref> An estimated 41% of the gross came from IMAX, 3D and premium large format screenings which began at 6&nbsp;pm, while the rest\u201459%\u2014came from regular 2D shows which began at 7&nbsp;pm.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-selling-out-1202045224/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Gorgeous on Thursday With $16.3M, Beats 'Furious 7' \u2013 Friday AM Update|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170320230239/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-selling-out-1202045224/|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> The numbers were considered more impressive given that the film played during a school week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/17/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-nabs-monstreous-16-3m-thursday/|title=Box Office: 'Beauty And The Beast' Nabs Monstreous $16.3M Thursday|author=Scott Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317213659/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/17/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-nabs-monstreous-16-3m-thursday/|archivedate=March 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn its opening day, the film made $63.8&nbsp;million from 4,210 theaters across 9,200 screens, marking the third biggest in the month of March, trailing behind ''Batman v Superman'' ($81.5&nbsp;million) and ''[[The Hunger Games (film)|The Hunger Games]]'' ($67&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-2-1202011524/|title=Box Office: 'Beauty and the Beast' Belts Out $64 Million on Friday|author=Seth Kelley|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=March 18, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318164740/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-2-1202011524/|archivedate=March 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-selling-out-1202045224/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Dazzling With $173M+ Opening; Bound To Set Records For Pre-Summer, Bill Condon & Emma Watson|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=March 18, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170320230239/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-selling-out-1202045224/|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> It was also the biggest opening day ever for a film that wasn't PG-13, displacing the $58&nbsp;million opening Wednesday of ''Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince''. Its opening day alone (which includes Thursday's previews) almost matched the entire opening weekend of previous Disney live-action films, ''Maleficent'' ($69.4&nbsp;million) and ''[[Cinderella (2015 Disney film)|Cinderella]]'' ($67.9&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/18/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-waltzes-to-beastly-63-7m-friday-for-possible-170m-weekend/|title=Box Office: 'Beauty And The Beast' Waltzes To Beastly $64M Friday For Possible $170M+ Weekend|author=Scott Mendelson|magazine=[[Forbes]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=March 18, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318170435/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/18/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-waltzes-to-beastly-63-7m-friday-for-possible-170m-weekend/|archivedate=March 18, 2017}}</ref> Unlike all previous four Disney live-action films witnessing a hike on their second day, Saturday, ''Beauty and the Beast'' actually fell 2%, nevertheless, the dip was paltry, and the grosses are so much greater in comparison to the other titles.<ref name=\"DOM\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-selling-out-1202045224/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Twirling To $174M+; Beats 'Harry Potter' & 'Batman V. Superman'; Can It Go Higher? \u2013 Sunday Final|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170320230239/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-selling-out-1202045224/|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> Earning a total of $174.8&nbsp;million on its opening weekend, it defied all expectations and went on to set numerous notable records.<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/20/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-topped-batman-v-superman-and-iron-man-3|title=Box Office: Disney's 'Beauty And The Beast' Debut Topped 'Batman V Superman' And 'Iron Man 3'|author=Scott Mendelson|magazine=Forbes|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817084201/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/20/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-topped-batman-v-superman-and-iron-man-3/|archivedate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> This includes the biggest opening of the year as well as the biggest for the month of March and pre-summer/spring opening, beating ''Batman v Superman'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/month/?mo=03&p=.htm|title=TOP OPENING WEEKENDS BY MONTH \u2013 MARCH |website=Box Office Mojo |access-date=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316054849/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/month/?mo=03&p=.htm|archivedate=March 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/byseason.htm?season=Spring&p=.htm|title=TOP OPENING WEEKENDS BY SEASON \u2013 SPRING|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170319172216/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/byseason.htm?season=Spring&p=.htm|archivedate=March 19, 2017}}</ref> the biggest start ever for a PG title (also for a family film), surpassing ''[[Finding Dory]]'' until it was later surpassed by ''[[Incredibles 2]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/mpaa.htm?page=PG&p=.htm|title=TOP OPENING WEEKENDS BY MPAA RATING|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320011013/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/mpaa.htm?page=PG&p=.htm|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> the biggest debut of all time for a female-led film, ahead of ''[[The Hunger Games: Catching Fire]]'',<ref name=\"5R\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-box-office-5-biggest-records-broken-987221|title='Beauty and the Beast' Box Office: 5 Biggest Records Broken|author=Pamela McClintock|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910172755/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/beauty-beast-box-office-5-biggest-records-broken-987221|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> the biggest for a Disney live-action adaptation, ahead of ''[[Alice in Wonderland (2010 film)|Alice in Wonderland]]''<ref name=\"5R\"/> and the biggest musical debut ever, supplanting ''[[Pitch Perfect 2]]''. Furthermore, it is also Watson's highest-opening, beating ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2]]'' same with [[Emma Thompson]], director [[Bill Condon]]'s biggest debut ever ahead of ''[[The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn \u2013 Part 2]]'' and the biggest outside of summer, save for ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'', not accounting for inflation.<ref name=\"Forbes\" />\n\nIt became the forty-third film to debut with over $100&nbsp;million and the fifteenth film to open above $150&nbsp;million. Its three-day opening alone surpassed the entire original North American run of the first film ($146&nbsp;million; before the 3D re-release), instantly becoming the second-biggest film of the year, behind ''Logan'' ($184&nbsp;million), and the second-highest-grossing musical, behind ''[[Grease (film)|Grease]]''{{'}}s $188&nbsp;million cumulative gross in 1978.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/19/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-opens-to-record-170m-u-s-350m-global-weekend/|title=Box Office: 'Beauty And The Beast' Nabs Record $170M U.S., $350M Global Debut|author=Scott Mendelson|magazine=Forbes|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170319180335/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/19/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-opens-to-record-170m-u-s-350m-global-weekend/|archivedate=March 19, 2017}}</ref> Out of the total ticket sales, 70% came from 2D showings thus signifying that people who don't go to theaters frequently came out in bulk to watch the film. About 26% of the remaining tickets were for 3D. IMAX accounted for 7% ($12.5&nbsp;million) of the total weekend's gross, setting a new record for a PG title, ahead of ''Alice in Wonderland'' ($12.1&nbsp;million) while PLF repped 11% of the box office.<ref name=\"DOM\"/> The film's opening day demographic, around 70% were female, dropping to 60% through the weekend.<ref name=\"5R\"/> According polling service [[PostTrak]], about 84% of American parents who saw the film on its opening day said they would \"definitely\" recommend it for families.<ref name=\"Jake Coyle\">{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2017/03/19/beauty-and-the-beast-170-million-debut-sets-box-office-record/99380216/|title='Beauty and the Beast' roars to No. 1 with monstrous $170M in box office|author=Jake Coyle|newspaper=[[USA Today]]|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170319182851/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2017/03/19/beauty-and-the-beast-170-million-debut-sets-box-office-record/99380216/|archivedate=March 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Brent Lang\">{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/box-office/beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-box-office-1202011723/|title='Beauty and the Beast': 5 Reasons the Disney Fantasy Scored at the Box Office|author=Brent Lang|magazine=Variety|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320004549/http://variety.com/2017/film/box-office/beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-box-office-1202011723/|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> The film's opening was credited to positive [[word of mouth]] from audiences, good reviews from critics, effective marketing which sold the title not just as a family film but also as a romantic drama, the cast's star power (namely [[Emma Watson]]), lack of competition, being the first family film since ''[[The Lego Batman Movie]]'' a month earlier, nostalgia, and the success and ubiquity of the first film and Disney's brand.<ref name=\"Jake Coyle\"/><ref name=\"Brent Lang\"/>\n\nOn Monday, its fourth day of release, the film fell precipitously by 72% earning $13.5&nbsp;million. The steep fall was due to a limited marketplace where only 11% K-12 and 15% colleges were off per [[ComScore]]. Nevertheless, it is the second-biggest March Monday, behind ''Batman v Superman'' ($15&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-second-bests-march-monday-box-office-batman-v-superman-1202047652/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Continues B.O. Dance With Second-Best Monday in March|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 21, 2017|accessdate=March 21, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170322014328/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-second-bests-march-monday-box-office-batman-v-superman-1202047652/|archivedate=March 22, 2017}}</ref> This was followed by the biggest March and pre-summer Tuesday with $17.8&nbsp;million, a 32% increase from its previous day. The same day, the film passed $200&nbsp;million in ticket sales.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-best-tuesday-before-summer-box-office-200-million-1202048388/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Hits A High Note With Best Pre-Summer Tuesday, Crosses $200M|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 22, 2017|accessdate=March 22, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170322154648/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-best-tuesday-before-summer-box-office-200-million-1202048388/|archivedate=March 22, 2017}}</ref> It earned $228.6&nbsp;million in the first week of release, the sixth-biggest seven-day gross of all time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/24/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-ends-first-week-just-below-500m/|title=Box Office: 'Beauty And The Beast' Ends First Week Just Below $500M|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326231618/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/24/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-ends-first-week-just-below-500m/|archivedate=March 26, 2017}}</ref> In its [[Second weekend in box office performance|second weekend]], the film continued to maintain the top positioning and fell gradually by 48% earning another $90.4&nbsp;million to register the fourth-biggest second weekend of all time, and the third-biggest for Disney.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/moreweekends.htm?page=2&p=.htm|title=TOP WEEKENDS: 2ND \u2013 12TH|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=March 27, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091202155351/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/moreweekends.htm?page=2&p=.htm|archivedate=December 2, 2009}}</ref> In terms of percentage drop, its 48% decline is the third-smallest drop for any film opening above $125&nbsp;million (behind ''Finding Dory'' and ''The Force Awakens'').<ref name=\"MUSIC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/28/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-waltzes-past-700m-worldwide|title=Box Office: 'Beauty And The Beast' Waltzes Past $700M Worldwide|author=Scott Mendelson|work=Forbes|date=March 28, 2017|accessdate=March 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808043031/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/03/28/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-waltzes-past-700m-worldwide/|archivedate=August 8, 2017}}</ref> The hold was notable considering how the film was able to fend off three new wide releases: ''[[Power Rangers (film)|Power Rangers]]'', ''[[Life (2017 film)|Life]]'', and ''[[Chips (film)|CHiPs]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_FILM_BOX_OFFICE?SITE=AP|title=BOX OFFICE TOP 20: 'BEAUTY' ADDS $90.4 MILLION IN WEEKEND 2|publisher=[[Associated Press]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170329142322/http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_FILM_BOX_OFFICE?SITE=AP|archivedate=March 29, 2017}}</ref> As a result, it passed the $300&nbsp;million threshold becoming the first film of 2017 the pass said mark.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/03/26/box-office-report-beauty-beast-power-rangers/|title=Box office report: Beauty and the Beast doubles Power Rangers' weekend gross|author=Joey Nolfi|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=March 26, 2017|accessdate=March 29, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328185836/http://ew.com/movies/2017/03/26/box-office-report-beauty-beast-power-rangers/|archivedate=March 28, 2017}}</ref> The film grossed $45.4&nbsp;million in its third weekend, finally being overtaken for the top spot by newcomer ''[[The Boss Baby]]'' ($50.2&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/ghost-in-the-shell-scarlett-johansson-boss-baby-beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-1202056616/ |title='Boss Baby' Cleans 'Beauty and the Beast's Clock with $51M+ Opening; 'Ghost' Shell-Shocked at $20M+ |accessdate=April 2, 2017 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170401142137/http://deadline.com/2017/03/ghost-in-the-shell-scarlett-johansson-boss-baby-beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-1202056616/ |archivedate=April 1, 2017  }}</ref> On April 4, 2017, its nineteenth day of release, it passed the $400&nbsp;million threshold becoming the first film of 2017 to do so.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/beauty-and-the-beast-crosses-900-million-worldwide-box-office-400-million-domestic-1202062137/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Enchants $900M at WW Box Office; Crosses $400M Domestic|accessdate=April 6, 2017|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910173547/http://deadline.com/2017/04/beauty-and-the-beast-crosses-900-million-worldwide-box-office-400-million-domestic-1202062137/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> By its fourth weekend, the film began was playing in 3,969 cinemas, a fall of 241 theaters from its previous weekend. Of those, approximately 1,200 cinemas were sing-along versions. It earned $26.3&nbsp;million (\u221248%) and retained second place. By comparison, previous Disney films ''[[Moana (2016 film)|Moana]]'' (\u22128%) and ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]'' (\u22122%) both witnessed mild percentage declines the weekend their sing-alone versions were released.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/07/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-ends-week-three-with-920-million/ |title=Box Office: 'Beauty and the Beast' Ends Week Three with $920 Million|author=Scott Mendelson|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 7, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017}}</ref> Its seventh weekend of release was in contemporaneous with another Emma Watson-starring new film ''[[The Circle (2017 film)|The Circle]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/04/emma-watson-the-circle-the-fate-of-the-furious-box-office-upset|title=How a Flashy Blockbuster and an Indian Fantasy Bested Emma Watson at the Box Office|author=Emma Stefansky|work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910174037/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/04/emma-watson-the-circle-the-fate-of-the-furious-box-office-upset|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> That weekend, ''The Circle'' was number four, while ''Beauty and the Beast'' was at number six.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/emma-watson-the-circle-fate-of-the-furious-weekend-box-office-how-to-be-a-latin-lover-1202079002/|title='Latin Lover' Sets $12M Pantelion Record, 'Baahubali 2' Mighty With $10M+, 'Circle' Is A Square As 'F8' Leads Listless Weekend|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=May 1, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910174144/http://deadline.com/2017/04/emma-watson-the-circle-fate-of-the-furious-weekend-box-office-how-to-be-a-latin-lover-1202079002/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> By May 28, the film had earned over $500&nbsp;million in ticket sales becoming the first film of 2017 (until it was later surpassed by ''The Last Jedi''),<ref>{{cite news |last=Hill |first=Libby |title='Star Wars: The Last Jedi' unseats 'Beauty and the Beast' as highest-grossing film of 2017 |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-box-office-star-wars-new-years-eve-20171231-story.html |date=December 31, 2017 |access-date=January 1, 2018 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231211940/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-box-office-star-wars-new-years-eve-20171231-story.html |archivedate=December 31, 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=The Associated Press |author-link=Associated Press |title='Star Wars: The Last Jedi' passes 'Beauty and the Beast' as top 2017 earner |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/star-wars-passes-beauty-beast-top-2017-earner-article-1.3729509 |date=December 31, 2017 |access-date=January 1, 2018 |newspaper=[[New York Daily News]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231211829/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/star-wars-passes-beauty-beast-top-2017-earner-article-1.3729509 |archivedate=December 31, 2017  }}</ref> the third female-led film (after ''The Force Awakens'' and ''Rogue One'' followed by ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'' and ''The Last Jedi'') and the eighth overall film in cinematic history to pass the mark.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/05/28/box-office-alien-covenant-suffers-brutal-71-drop-as-guardians-2-tops-guardians/|title=Box Office: 'Alien: Covenant' Suffers Brutal 71% Drop As 'Guardians 2' Tops 'Guardians'|author=Scott Mendelson|magazine=Forbes|date=May 28, 2017|accessdate=May 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808042536/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/05/28/box-office-alien-covenant-suffers-brutal-71-drop-as-guardians-2-tops-guardians/|archivedate=August 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-3-1202446806/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Crosses $500 Million Milestone at Domestic Box Office|author=Seth Kelley|magazine=Variety|date=May 28, 2017|accessdate=May 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170528173800/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-3-1202446806/|archivedate=May 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/box-office/wonder-woman-beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-1202504023/|title=Why 'Wonder Woman' and 'Beauty and the Beast' Should Lead to More Female-Centered Films|author=Seth Kelley|magazine=Variety|date=July 23, 2017|accessdate=August 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813044041/http://variety.com/2017/film/box-office/wonder-woman-beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-1202504023/|archivedate=August 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/last-jedi-jumanji-new-years-weekend-box-office-2018-1202233711/|title='Last Jedi', 'Jumanji' Propelling 2017 Box Office To $11B+ Year \u2013 AM Update|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=December 31, 2017|accessdate=December 31, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231071613/http://deadline.com/2017/12/last-jedi-jumanji-new-years-weekend-box-office-2018-1202233711/|archivedate=December 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIt has already become the biggest March release, dethroning ''[[The Hunger Games (film)|The Hunger Games]]'' (2012),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/04/12/box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-may-cross-1-billion-today/|title=Box Office: 'Beauty And The Beast' Should Cross $1 Billion Today|author=Scott Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> the biggest musical film (both animated and live-action),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/genres/chart/?id=musical.htm|title=Musical|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=May 29, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170523155712/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/genres/chart/?id=musical.htm|archivedate=May 23, 2017}}</ref> as well as the biggest film of 2017 (alongside ''The Last Jedi'').<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?yr=2017|title=2017 DOMESTIC GROSSES|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=April 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413234653/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?yr=2017|archivedate=April 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Other countries====\nOutside the US and Canada, the film began playing on Thursday, March 16, 2017. Through Sunday, March 19, it had a total international opening of $182.3&nbsp;million from 55 markets, 44 of which were major territories, far exceeding initial estimations of $100&nbsp;million and opened at No. 1 in virtually all markets except Vietnam, Turkey, and India. Its launch is the second-biggest for the month of March, behind ''Batman v Superman'' ($256.5&nbsp;million). In IMAX, it recorded the biggest debut for a PG-rated title (although it carried varying certificate amongst different markets) with $8.5&nbsp;million from 649 screens, the second-biggest for a PG title behind ''[[The Jungle Book (2016 film)|The Jungle Book]]''.<ref name=\"INTL\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-logan-kong-skull-island-international-box-office-1202046567/|title='Beauty and the Beast' A$1B Belle WW?: Bow Enchants With Bigger $357M Global, $182M Offshore \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 21, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910174838/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-logan-kong-skull-island-international-box-office-1202046567/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> In its second weekend, it fell just by 35% earning another $120.6&nbsp;million and maintaining its first position hold. It added major markets like France and Australia.<ref name=\"W119\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-kong-skull-island-power-rangers-china-weekend-box-office-international-1202052444/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Nears $700M WW; 'Kong' Has Mighty $72M China Bow, Tops $250M Offshore \u2013 International Box Office|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327073145/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-kong-skull-island-power-rangers-china-weekend-box-office-international-1202052444/|archivedate=March 27, 2017}}</ref> It topped the international box office for three consecutive weekends<ref name=\"WW3\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/beauty-and-the-beast-kong-skull-island-ghost-in-the-shell-boss-baby-china-international-box-office-1202058460/|title='Beauty' Is $876M Beast WW; 'Ghost in the Shell' Sells $40M Offshore; 'Kong' Sets WB China Record \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 2, 2017|accessdate=April 4, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910175529/http://deadline.com/2017/04/beauty-and-the-beast-kong-skull-island-ghost-in-the-shell-boss-baby-china-international-box-office-1202058460/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> before finally being dethroned by ''[[Ghost in the Shell (2017 film)|Ghost in the Shell]]'' and ''[[The Boss Baby]]'' in its fourth weekend. Despite the fall, the film helped Disney push past the $1&nbsp;billion threshold internationally for the first time in 2017.<ref name=\"Tot\"/><ref name=\"W4\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/beauty-and-the-beast-ghost-in-the-shell-boss-baby-kong-china-international-box-office-weekend-1202066154/|title='Ghost in the Shell' Rises To $93M Offshore; 'Beauty and the Beast' Tops $977M Global \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 9, 2017|accessdate=April 11, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910175844/http://deadline.com/2017/04/beauty-and-the-beast-ghost-in-the-shell-boss-baby-kong-china-international-box-office-weekend-1202066154/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIt scored the biggest opening day of the year in Hong Kong and the Philippines, the biggest March Thursday in Italy ($1&nbsp;million, also the biggest Disney Thursday debut), the biggest March opening day in Austria, and the second-biggest in Germany ($1.1&nbsp;million), Disney's biggest March in Denmark, the biggest Disney live-action debut in China ($12.6&nbsp;million), the UK ($6.2&nbsp;million), Mexico ($2.4&nbsp;million) and Brazil ($1.8&nbsp;million) and the third-biggest in South Korea with $1.2&nbsp;million, behind only ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End]]'' and ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: On Stranger Tides]]''.<ref name=\"DD\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-opening-international-box-office-1202045514/|title='Beauty and the Beast' A Monster With $52M Offshore Through Friday, $115.6M Global \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=Deadline.com|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=March 18, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318040350/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-opening-international-box-office-1202045514/|archivedate=March 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Beauty and the Beast' continues box-office reign|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3031475|date=March 28, 2017|accessdate=March 28, 2017|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328003437/http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3031475|archivedate=March 28, 2017}}</ref> In terms of opening weekend, the largest debut came from China ($44.8&nbsp;million), followed by the UK ($24.3&nbsp;million), Korea ($11.8&nbsp;million), Mexico ($11.8&nbsp;million), Australia ($11.1&nbsp;million), Brazil ($11&nbsp;million), Germany ($10.7&nbsp;million), France ($8.4&nbsp;million), Italy ($7.6&nbsp;million), Philippines ($6.3&nbsp;million), Russia ($6&nbsp;million), and Spain ($5.8&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"INTL\"/><ref name=\"W119\"/>\n\nIn the United Kingdom and Ireland, the film recorded the biggest opening ever for a PG-rated film, the biggest Disney live-action opening of all time, the biggest March opening weekend, the biggest opening for a musical (ahead of 2012's ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]''), the number one opening of 2017 to date and the fifth-biggest-ever overall with \u00a319.7&nbsp;million ($24.5&nbsp;million) from 639 theatres and almost twice that of ''The Jungle Book'' (\u00a39.9&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/mar/21/uk-box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-kong-skull-island-get-out|title=Beauty and the Beast waltzes its way to the top of the UK box office|author=Charles Gant|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=March 21, 2017|accessdate=March 22, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170321212830/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/mar/21/uk-box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-kong-skull-island-get-out|archivedate=March 21, 2017}}</ref> This included the second-biggest Saturday ever (\u00a37.9&nbsp;million), only behind ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/mar/19/beauty-and-the-beast-smashes-the-box-office-in-opening-weekend|title=Beauty and the Beast smashes the box office in opening weekend|author=(Press Release)|newspaper=The Guardian|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 22, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170321155836/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/mar/19/beauty-and-the-beast-smashes-the-box-office-in-opening-weekend|archivedate=March 21, 2017}}</ref> It witnessed a decline in its second weekend, earning \u00a312.33&nbsp;million ($15.4&nbsp;million). Though the film was falling at a faster rate than ''The Jungle Book'', it had already surpassed the said film and its second weekend is the third-biggest ever (behind the two [[List of James Bond films|James Bond films]] ''[[Skyfall]]'' (2012) and ''[[Spectre (2015 film)|Spectre]]'').<ref name=\"W119\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/mar/28/uk-box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-chips-life-power-rangers|title=Beauty and the Beast magic helps UK box office survive the spring sunshine|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328145709/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/mar/28/uk-box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-chips-life-power-rangers|archivedate=March 28, 2017}}</ref> In India, despite facing heavy competitions from four new Hindi releases, two Tamils films and a Malayalam and a Punjabi release, the film managed to take an occupancy of 15% on its opening day, an impressive feat despite tremendous competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/beauty-the-beasts-opens-better-than-aa-gaya-hero-trapped-machine-mantra/|title=Beauty & The Beast Opens Better Than Aa Gaya Hero, Trapped, Machine & Mantra|publisher=[[Koimoi]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317155927/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/beauty-the-beasts-opens-better-than-aa-gaya-hero-trapped-machine-mantra/|archivedate=March 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=2789|title=Beauty and the Beast Opens Better Than Hindi Releases|website=[[Box Office India]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320052404/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=2789|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/03/15/rajkummar-rao-faces-a-lone-battle-for-survival-in-trapped/|title=Rajkummar Rao Faces A Lone Battle For Survival In 'Trapped'|author=Don Groves|magazine=Forbes|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316023008/https://www.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/03/15/rajkummar-rao-faces-a-lone-battle-for-survival-in-trapped/|archivedate=March 16, 2017}}</ref> It earned around {{INRConvert|15|m}} nett on its opening day from an estimated 600 screens which is more than the three Hindi releases\u2014''[[Machine (2017 film)|Machine]]'', ''[[Trapped (2016 Indian film)|Trapped]]'', and ''[[Aa Gaya Hero]]\u2014''combined.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=2792|title=Beauty and the Beast Beats Hindi Films Combined|website=[[Box Office India]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320052457/https://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=2792|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> Disney reported a total of {{INRConvert|92.6|m}} gross for its opening weekend there. It was ahead of all new releases and second overall behind Bollywood film ''[[Badrinath Ki Dulhania]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/03/19/varun-dhawan-and-alia-bhatt-outrun-beauty-and-the-beast-to-reign-again-in-india/|title=Varun Dhawan and Alia Bhatt Outrun 'Beauty and the Beast' To Reign Again in India|author=Don Groves|magazine=Forbes|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320015400/https://www.forbes.com/sites/dongroves/2017/03/19/varun-dhawan-and-alia-bhatt-outrun-beauty-and-the-beast-to-reign-again-in-india/|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/box-office/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-collection-first-weekend/articleshow/57730319.cms|title='Beauty and the Beast' box-office collection first weekend|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181222225114/https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/box-office/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-collection-first-weekend/articleshow/57730319.cms|archive-date=December 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/beauty-the-beast-enjoys-a-good-1st-weekend-at-the-box-office-in-india/|title=Beauty & The Beast Enjoys A Good 1st Weekend at the Box Office in India|publisher=[[Koimoi.com]]|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320100130/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/beauty-the-beast-enjoys-a-good-1st-weekend-at-the-box-office-in-india/|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> In Russia, despite receiving a restrictive 16 rating, the film managed to deliver a very successful opening with $6&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/box-office/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-records-1202011676/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Debuts to Magical $350 Million Globally|author=Brent Lang|magazine=Variety|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 19, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170319172758/http://variety.com/2017/film/box-office/beauty-and-the-beast-box-office-records-1202011676/|archivedate=March 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn China, expectations were high for the film. The release date was announced on January 24, giving Disney and local distributor [[China Film Group Corporation]] ample time\u2014around two months\u2014to market the film nationwide. The release date was strategically chosen to coincide with [[White Day]]. Preliminary reports suggested that it could open to $40\u201360&nbsp;million in its opening weekend. Largely driven by young women, its opening day pre-sales outpaced that of ''[[The Jungle Book (2016 film)|The Jungle Book]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/beauty-looks-like-a-beast/|title=On Screen China: 'Beauty' Looks Like a Beast|author=Jonathan Papish|publisher=China Film Insider|date=March 15, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318003018/http://chinafilminsider.com/beauty-looks-like-a-beast/|archivedate=March 18, 2017}}</ref> The original film was, however, never widely popular in the country.<ref name=\"CFI\">{{cite web|url=http://chinafilminsider.com/first-place-for-beautystill-less-than-best/|title=China Box Office: First Place For 'Beauty' Still Less Than Best|author=Jonathan Papish|publisher=China Film Insider|date=March 22, 2017|accessdate=March 23, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323143307/http://chinafilminsider.com/first-place-for-beautystill-less-than-best/|archivedate=March 23, 2017}}</ref> Although China has occasionally blocked gay-themed content from streaming video services, in this case, Chinese censors decided to leave the gay scene intact. According to local box office tracker Ent Group, the film grossed an estimated $12.1&nbsp;million on its opening day (Friday), representing 70% of the total receipts. Including previews, it made a total of $14.5&nbsp;million from 100,000 screenings, which is 43% of all screenings in the country.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/uncensored-beauty-and-the-beast-opens-solidly-in-china-1202010786/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Opens Strong in China With 'Gay Moment' Intact|author=Patrick Frater|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317160410/http://variety.com/2017/film/asia/uncensored-beauty-and-the-beast-opens-solidly-in-china-1202010786/|archivedate=March 17, 2017}}</ref> It climbed to $18.5&nbsp;million on Saturday (102,700 showings) for a three-day total of $42.6&nbsp;million, securing 60% of the total marketplace. Disney on the other hand reported a different figure of $44.8&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-box-office-beauty-beast-opens-45m-gay-moment-uncut-987254|title=China Box Office: 'Beauty and the Beast' Opens to $45M, With Gay Moment Uncut|author=Patrick Brzeski|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320040955/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-box-office-beauty-beast-opens-45m-gay-moment-uncut-987254|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/china-box-office-beauty-weekend-1202011767/|title=China Box Office: 'Beauty' Dominates Weekend|author=Patrick Frater|magazine=Variety|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320082628/http://variety.com/2017/film/asia/china-box-office-beauty-weekend-1202011767/|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref> Either-way, it recorded the second-biggest opening for a Disney live-action film,<ref name=\"CFI\"/> with $3.4&nbsp;million coming from 386 IMAX screens.<ref name=\"INTL\"/> Japan\u2014a huge Disney market\u2014served as the film's final market and opened there on April 21.<ref name=\"W119\"/> It debuted with a better-than-expected $12.5&nbsp;million on its opening weekend helping the film push past the $1.1&nbsp;billion threshold. An estimated $1.1&nbsp;million came from IMAX screenings, the fourth-biggest ever in the country.<ref name=\"Japs\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-8-beauty-beast-weekend-china-international-box-office-1202075671/|title='Fate of the Furious' Fires Up $745M Offshore, $908M WW; Tops 'Transformers' In China \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 23, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910180652/http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-8-beauty-beast-weekend-china-international-box-office-1202075671/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/asia/japan-box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-opens-strongly-1202393550/|title=Japan Box Office: 'Beauty and the Beast' Opens Strongly Ahead of Golden Week|author=Mark Schilling|magazine=Variety|date=April 23, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170425205005/http://variety.com/2017/film/asia/japan-box-office-beauty-and-the-beast-opens-strongly-1202393550/|archivedate=April 25, 2017}}</ref> The two-day gross was $9.7&nbsp;million, outstripping ''Frozen''{{'}}s previous record of $9.5&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atimes.com/article/beast-best-japan-fate-furious-drives-china-south-korea/|title=Beast is Best in Japan; Fast & Furious drives China, Korea|author=Russell Edwards|publisher=[[Asia Times]]|date=April 25, 2017|accessdate=April 25, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170425190141/http://www.atimes.com/article/beast-best-japan-fate-furious-drives-china-south-korea/|archivedate=April 25, 2017}}</ref> Due to positive reviews, good word-of-mouth and benefitting from the [[Golden Week (Japan)|Golden Week]], the film saw a 9% increase on its second weekend. The hold was strong enough to fend off newcomer ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]'' from securing the top spot. The total there is now over $98&nbsp;million after seven weekends<ref name=\"GotG\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-fate-of-the-furious-baahubali-2-china-international-box-office-1202079772/|title='Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 2' Zooms With $101.2M Bow \u2013 International Box Office|author=Tartaglione|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=April 30, 2017|accessdate=April 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910181122/http://deadline.com/2017/05/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-fate-of-the-furious-baahubali-2-china-international-box-office-1202079772/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Jap60\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-marvel-11-billion-fate-of-the-furious-baahubali-international-china-box-office-weekend-1202086302/|title='Guardians 2' Notches $428M Global, Lifts MCU Past $11B; 'Furious 8' Tops $950M Offshore \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 7, 2017|accessdate=May 7, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170508130012/http://deadline.com/2017/05/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-marvel-11-billion-fate-of-the-furious-baahubali-international-china-box-office-weekend-1202086302/|archivedate=May 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://m.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/05/14/box-office-guardians-2-snags-63m-weekend-for-630-6m-worldwide/|title=Box Office: 'Guardians 2' Snags $63M Weekend For $631M Worldwide|author=Scott Mendelson|magazine=Forbes|date=May 14, 2017|accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref> and is the biggest film release of the year and, overall, the eleventh-biggest of all time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/intl/japan/yearly/|title=Japan Yearly Box Office (2017)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=May 8, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707075345/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/intl/japan/yearly/|archivedate=July 7, 2017}}</ref> It topped the box office there for eight consecutive weekends.<ref name=\"7Seven\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/wonder-woman-opening-box-office-results-international-1202105707/|title='Wonder Woman' Leaps To $125M Offshore, $228M Global Debut \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=June 5, 2017|accessdate=June 6, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170604232323/http://deadline.com/2017/06/wonder-woman-opening-box-office-results-international-1202105707/|archivedate=June 4, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/the-mummy-wonder-woman-international-box-office-weekend-results-1202111212/|title='The Mummy' Unearths $141M Offshore, $172.3M Global; 'Wonder Woman' Flies To $232M at International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=June 12, 2017|accessdate=June 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611183311/http://deadline.com/2017/06/the-mummy-wonder-woman-international-box-office-weekend-results-1202111212/|archivedate=June 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe only markets where the film did not top the weekend charts were Vietnam (behind ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]''), Turkey (with two local films and ''Logan'' ahead) and India (where ''[[Badrinath Ki Dulhania]]'' retained No. 1).<ref name=\"INTL\"/> It topped the box office for four straight weekends in Germany, Korea, Austria, Finland, Poland, Portugal, Brazil, Venezuela, Bolivia, Switzerland and the UK (exclusive of previews).<ref name=\"W4\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/apr/11/the-boss-baby-beauty-beast-uk-box-office|title=The Boss Baby makes a dummy of UK box-office competition|author=Charles Gant|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=April 11, 2017|accessdate=April 12, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910180110/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/apr/11/the-boss-baby-beauty-beast-uk-box-office|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> In the Philippines, it emerged as the [[List of highest-grossing films in the Philippines|most successful commercial film of all time]]\u2014both local and foreign\u2014with over $13.5&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"PS\">{{cite news|url=http://m.philstar.com/314196/show/61a4ad8622e425f9081767f84d3b13fa/|title='Beauty and the Beast' smashes Philippines' all-time box office records|newspaper=[[The Philippine Star]]|date=April 13, 2017|accessdate=April 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413154544/http://m.philstar.com/314196/show/61a4ad8622e425f9081767f84d3b13fa/|archivedate=April 13, 2017}}</ref> In just five weeks, the film became one of the top 10 [[List of highest-grossing films in the United Kingdom|highest-grossing film of all time in the United Kingdom and Ireland]], ahead of all but one ''Harry Potter'' film (''Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2'') and all three [[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' films]] (which also starred [[Ian McKellen]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/apr/19/fast-furious-8-barrels-past-boss-baby-to-top-of-uk-box-office|title=Fast & Furious 8 barrels past Boss Baby to top of UK box office|author=Charles Gant|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=April 19, 2017|accessdate=April 20, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910180553/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/apr/19/fast-furious-8-barrels-past-boss-baby-to-top-of-uk-box-office|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> It is currently the eighth-biggest grosser with \u00a370.1&nbsp;million ($90&nbsp;million), overtaking ''Mamma Mia!'' to become the biggest musical production ever there.<ref name=\"Japs\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/may/03/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-uk-box-office-lady-macbeth-handmaiden-their-finest|title=Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 2 blows away UK box office with huge debut|author=Charles Gant|newspaper=The Guardian|date=May 3, 2017|accessdate=May 3, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910180723/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2017/may/03/guardians-of-the-galaxy-vol-2-uk-box-office-lady-macbeth-handmaiden-their-finest|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> The biggest international earning markets following the UK are Japan ($108&nbsp;million), China ($85.8&nbsp;million), Brazil ($41.5&nbsp;million), Korea ($37.5&nbsp;million), and Australia ($35&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"7Seven\"/> In Europe alone, the cumulative total is $267&nbsp;million, which led it to become the second-highest-grossing film in the past year (behind ''[[Rogue One|Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]'').<ref name=\"Japs\"/><ref name=\"GotG\"/><ref name=\"F58\">{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-record-opening-weekend-logan-beauty-and-the-beast-international-box-office-1202070697/|title='Fate of the Furious' Smokes Records With $432.3M Overseas Bow; $532.5M Worldwide \u2013 International Box Office|author=Nancy Tartaglione and Anita Busch|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 16, 2017|accessdate=April 17, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910180936/http://deadline.com/2017/04/fate-of-the-furious-record-opening-weekend-logan-beauty-and-the-beast-international-box-office-1202070697/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\n''Beauty and the Beast'' received positive reviews from critics, with particular praise going to its cast (notably Watson and Stevens), visuals, [[Alan Menken]]'s musical score, songs, [[Jacqueline Durran]]'s costume design, production values, and faithfulness to the original animated film with a few elements of the [[Beauty and the Beast (musical)|Broadway musical version]], while the designs of the Beast and the servants' household object forms drew mixed reviews.<ref name=\"BeautyandtheBeastReview\">{{cite news|url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/entertainment/article138958938.html|date=March 16, 2017|title=Live-action 'Beauty and the Beast' is still enchanting (but the original is better)|work=[[The Charlotte Observer]]|publisher=Robert W. Butler|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910195915/http://www.charlotteobserver.com/entertainment/article138958938.html|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"BeautyandtheBeastCriticReview\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-reviews/beauty-and-the-beast-review-9971177|title=Beauty and the Beast review: Irresistible charm shows no one casts a spell quite like Disney|author=Chris Hunneysett|work=[[Daily Mirror]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=April 27, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910200005/http://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-reviews/beauty-and-the-beast-review-9971177|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> On [[review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 71% based on 368 reviews, with an [[average rating]] of 6.69/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"With an enchanting cast, beautifully crafted songs, and a painterly eye for detail, ''Beauty and the Beast'' offers a faithful yet fresh retelling that honors its beloved source material.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/beauty_and_the_beast_2017|title=Beauty and the Beast (2017)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171211204754/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/beauty_and_the_beast_2017/|archivedate=December 11, 2017|url-status=live|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a score of 65 out of 100, based on 47 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/beauty-and-the-beast-2017|title=Beauty and the Beast Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=April 14, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414050746/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/beauty-and-the-beast-2017|archivedate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> In [[CinemaScore]] polls, audiences gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale.<ref name=\"CinemaScore\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/CinemaScore/status/842972100898017280 |title=''Beauty and the Beast'' |publisher=[[CinemaScore]] on Twitter |date=March 17, 2017 |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910200145/https://twitter.com/CinemaScore/status/842972100898017280 |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-selling-out-1202045224/|title='Beauty and the Beast' Dazzling With $169M+ Opening; Bound To Set Records For Pre-Summer, Bill Condon & Emma Watson|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=March 18, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170320230239/http://deadline.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-weekend-box-office-selling-out-1202045224/|archivedate=March 20, 2017}}</ref>\n\nLeslie Felperin of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' wrote: \"It's a Michelin-triple-starred master class in patisserie skills that transforms the cinematic equivalent of a sugar rush into a kind of crystal-meth-like narcotic high that lasts about two hours.\" Felperin also praised the performances of Watson and Kline as well the special effects, costume designs and the sets, while commending the inclusion of Gad's character of LeFou as the first LGBT character in Disney.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/beauty-beast-review-982373|title = 'Beauty and the Beast': Film Review|author = Felperin, Leslie|work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date = March 3, 2017|accessdate = April 23, 2017|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170422073605/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/beauty-beast-review-982373|archivedate = April 22, 2017|df = mdy-all}}</ref> [[Owen Gleiberman]] of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', in his positive review of the film, wrote: \"It's a lovingly crafted movie, and in many ways a good one, but before that it's an enraptured piece of old-is-new nostalgia.\" Gleiberman compared Steven's character of the Beast to a royal version of the [[Joseph Merrick|titular character]] in ''[[The Elephant Man (film)|The Elephant Man]]'' and the 1946 version of the Beast in [[Jean Cocteau]]'s [[Beauty and the Beast (1946 film)|original adaptation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/beauty-and-the-beast-review-emma-watson-1202001341/|title=Film Review: 'Beauty and the Beast'|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Owen|last=Gleiberman|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=March 3, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303193248/http://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/beauty-and-the-beast-review-emma-watson-1202001341/|archivedate=March 3, 2017}}</ref> [[A. O. Scott]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'' praised the performances of both Watson and Stevens, and wrote: \"It looks good, moves gracefully and leaves a clean and invigorating aftertaste. I almost didn't recognize the flavor: I think the name for it is joy.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/03/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-review.html|date=March 3, 2017|title=Review: 'Beauty and the Beast' Revels in Joy and Enchantment|work=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=[[A. O. Scott]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910202201/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/03/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-review.html|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nLikewise, ''[[The Washington Post]]''{{'}}s [[Ann Hornaday]] complimented Watson's performance, describing it as \"alert and solemn\" while noting her singing ability as \"serviceable enough to get the job done\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/remake-of-beauty-and-the-beast-convincingly-springs-to-life/2017/03/16/9022737c-05bf-11e7-ad5b-d22680e18d10_story.html|date=March 16, 2017|title=Remake of 'Beauty and the Beast' convincingly springs to life|work=[[The Washington Post]]|publisher=Ann Hornaday|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317020342/https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/remake-of-beauty-and-the-beast-convincingly-springs-to-life/2017/03/16/9022737c-05bf-11e7-ad5b-d22680e18d10_story.html|archivedate=March 17, 2017}}</ref> [[Richard Roeper]] of ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' awarded the film three and a half out of five and lauded the performances of Watson and Thompson which he drew a comparison to [[Paige O'Hara]]'s and [[Angela Lansbury]]'s performances in the 1991 animated version while appreciating the performances of the other cast.  He also commented on the advantage of its using both motion capture and CGI technology, writing: \"Almost overwhelmingly lavish, beautifully staged and performed with exquisite timing and grace by the outstanding cast\".<ref name=\"CST\">{{cite web|url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/lavish-beauty-and-the-beast-true-as-it-can-be-to-original/|title=Lavish 'Beauty and the Beast' true as it can be to original|author=[[Richard Roeper]]|work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|date=March 15, 2017|accessdate=April 26, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910202458/http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/lavish-beauty-and-the-beast-true-as-it-can-be-to-original/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> Mike Ryan of ''[[Uproxx]]'' praised the cast, production design and the new songs while noting the film doesn't try anything different, saying: \"There's certainly nothing that new about this version of ''Beauty and the Beast'' (well, except it isn't a cartoon anymore), but it's a good recreation of a classic animated film that should leave most die-hards satisfied.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uproxx.com/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-review/ |title=The New 'Beauty and the Beast' Should Satisfy Most Fans |website=[[Uproxx]] |date=March 3, 2017 |accessdate=March 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910202646/http://uproxx.com/movies/beauty-and-the-beast-review/ |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref> In her A- review, Nancy Churnin of ''[[The Dallas Morning News]]'' praised the film's emotional and thematic depth, remarking: \"There's an emotional authenticity in director Bill Condon's live-action Beauty and the Beast film that helps you rediscover Disney's beloved 1991 animated film and 1994 stage show in fresh, stirring ways.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guidelive.com/movie-reviews/2017/03/15/beauty-beauty-beast-brings-fresh-resonance-tale-old-time|title='Beauty and the Beast' brings fresh resonance to 'a tale as old as time'|website=[[The Dallas Morning News]]|first=Nancy|last=Churnin|date=March 15, 2017|accessdate=May 31, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170718104306/https://www.guidelive.com/movie-reviews/2017/03/15/beauty-beauty-beast-brings-fresh-resonance-tale-old-time|archivedate=July 18, 2017}}</ref> [[James Berardinelli]] of ReelViews described the 2017 version as \"enthralling\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Berardinelli|first1=James|authorlink=James Berardinelli|title=''Beauty and the Beast'' (United States, 2017)|url=http://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/beauty-and-the-beast_1|accessdate=October 10, 2017|publisher=Reelviews|date=March 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170629050046/http://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/beauty-and-the-beast_1|archivedate=June 29, 2017}} {{rating|3|4}}</ref>\n\nBrian Truitt of ''[[USA Today]]'' commended the performances of Evans, Gad, McGregor and Thompson alongside Condon's affinity with musicals, the production design, visual effects featured in some of the song numbers including new songs made by the composers Alan Menken and Tim Rice, particularly ''Evermore'' which he described the new song with a potential for an [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2017/03/03/review-new-beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-dan-stevens/98649358/|date=March 17, 2017|title=Review: Rousing new 'Beauty and the Beast' is even better than the original|work=[[USA Today]]|publisher=Brian Truitt|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422213307/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2017/03/03/review-new-beauty-and-the-beast-emma-watson-dan-stevens/98649358/|archivedate=April 22, 2017}}</ref> [[Peter Travers]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' rated the film three out of four, deeming it an \"exhilarating gift\" while he remarked that \"''Beauty and the Beast'' does justice to Disney's animated classic, even if some of the magic is M.I.A (Missing in Action)\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/reviews/peter-travers-beauty-and-the-beast-movie-review-w471990|title='Beauty and the Beast' Review: Live-Action Disney Classic Still Tale as Old as Time|author=[[Peter Travers]]|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=March 17, 2017|accessdate=April 24, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910200643/http://www.rollingstone.com/movies/reviews/peter-travers-beauty-and-the-beast-movie-review-w471990|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> [[Stephanie Zacharek]] of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine gave a positive review with a description as \"Wild, Vivid and Crazy-Beautiful\" as she wrote \"Nearly everything about ''Beauty and the Beast'' is larger than life, to the point that watching it can be a little overwhelming.\" and added that \"it's loaded with feeling, almost like a brash interpretive dance expressing the passion and elation little girls (and some boys, too) must have felt upon seeing the earlier version.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4689999/beauty-and-the-beast-review/|title=REVIEW: The Reimagined Beauty and the Beast Is Wild, Vivid and Crazy-Beautiful|author=Zacharek, Stephanie|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=March 4, 2017|accessdate=April 26, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170426151627/http://time.com/4689999/beauty-and-the-beast-review/|archivedate=April 26, 2017}}</ref> The ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]''{{'}}s [[Mick LaSalle]] struck an affirmative tone, calling it one of the joys of 2017, stating that \"''Beauty and the Beast'' creates an air of enchantment from its first moments, one that lingers and builds and takes on qualities of warmth and generosity as it goes along\" while referring the film as \"beautiful\" and also praised the film for its emotional and psychological tone as well Steven's motion capture performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfchronicle.com/movies/article/Beauty-and-the-Beast-is-warm-and-enchanted-10998982.php|title=Enchanting 'Beauty and the Beast' looks like a winner|author=LaSalle, Mick|work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]]|date=March 13, 2017|accessdate=April 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170429000732/http://www.sfchronicle.com/movies/article/Beauty-and-the-Beast-is-warm-and-enchanted-10998982.php|archivedate=April 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\nTim Robey of ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' gave the film four out of five and wrote that \"It dazzles on this chocolate box of a picture that feels almost greedy yet to make this film work, down to a sugar-rush finale to grasp the nettle and make an out-an-out, bells-and-whistles musical\" while he praised the performances of Watson, McKellen, Thompson, McGregor, Evans and Gad.<ref>{{cite web|title=Beauty and the Beast review: Emma Watson dazzles in Disney's show-stopping chocolate box of a remake|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/0/beauty-beast-review-emma-watson-dazzles-disneys-show-stopping/|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|location=London|accessdate=March 17, 2017|date=March 17, 2017|first=Tim|last=Robey|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317035309/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/0/beauty-beast-review-emma-watson-dazzles-disneys-show-stopping/|archivedate=March 17, 2017}}</ref> Mark Hughes of ''[[Forbes]]'' also praised the film, which he wrote \"could revive the story in a faithful but entirely new and unique way elevating the material beyond expectations, establishing itself as a cinematic equal to the original\u201d.  He also complimented the importance of undertaking a renowned yet problematic [[Beauty and the Beast|masterpiece]] as well addressing changes in the elements of the story while acknowledging the film's effectiveness in resonating to the audiences.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/markhughes/2017/03/17/beauty-and-the-beast/|date=March 17, 2017|title='Beauty and the Beast' Magically Modernizes Classic Disney Fairy Tale|work=[[Forbes]]|publisher=Mark Hughes|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424014250/https://www.forbes.com/sites/markhughes/2017/03/17/beauty-and-the-beast/|archivedate=April 24, 2017}}</ref> Stephen Whitty of the ''[[New York Daily News]]'' called it \"this year's best new old musical\" and \"the most magical thing of all\" while describing Watson's performance of Belle as \"breakthrough\".<ref>{{cite web|title='Beauty and the Beast' a magical delight with Emma Watson: movie review|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/beauty-beast-magical-emma-watson-movie-review-article-1.2987850|work=[[New York Daily News]]|accessdate=November 30, 2017|date=March 3, 2017|first=Stephen|last=Whitty|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201035539/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/beauty-beast-magical-emma-watson-movie-review-article-1.2987850|archivedate=December 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nSeveral critics regarded the film as inferior to its [[Beauty and the Beast (1991 film)|1991 animated predecessor]]. David Sims of ''[[The Atlantic]]'' wrote that the 2017 film \"feels particularly egregious, in part, because it's so slavishly devoted to the original; every time it falls short of its predecessor (which is quite often), it's hard not to notice\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-remake-review/519603/ |title=Beauty and the Beast: A Tale as Old as Time, Told Worse |accessdate=September 1, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910202831/https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-remake-review/519603/ |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref> [[Michael Phillips (critic)|Michael Phillips]] of the ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' said that the 2017 film \"takes our knowledge and our interest in the material for granted. It zips from one number to another, throwing a ton of frenetically edited eye candy at the screen, charmlessly.\" Phillips wrote that the film featured some \"less conspicuously talented\" performers who are \"stuck doing karaoke, or motion-capture work of middling quality\", though he praised Kline's performance as the \"best, sweetest thing in the movie; he brings a sense of calm, droll authority\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/movies/ct-beauty-and-the-beast-review-20170313-column.html|title='Beauty and the Beast' review: Animated Disney musical's charms lost in translation|website=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=March 14, 2017|accessdate=March 14, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910202954/http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/movies/ct-beauty-and-the-beast-review-20170313-column.html|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> [[Peter Bradshaw]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' praised Watson's performance and wrote that the film was \"lit in that fascinatingly artificial honey-glow light, and it runs smoothly on rails\u2014the kind of rails that bring in and out the stage sets for the lucrative Broadway touring version.\" In the same newspaper, Wendy Ide criticized the film as \"ornate to the point of desperation\" in its attempt to emulate the animated film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/mar/03/beauty-and-the-beast-review-emma-watson-disney|title=Beauty and the Beast review&nbsp;\u2013 Emma Watson makes a perfect Belle in sugar-rush romance|last=Bradshaw|first=Peter|author-link=Peter Bradshaw|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=April 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170428055107/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/mar/03/beauty-and-the-beast-review-emma-watson-disney|archivedate=April 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/mar/19/beauty-and-the-beast-review-undeniably-arresting-emma-watson-josh-gad-bill-condon|title=Beauty and the Beast review&nbsp;\u2013 gilt complex|last=Ide|first=Wendy|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=March 19, 2017|accessdate=April 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170427104944/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/mar/19/beauty-and-the-beast-review-undeniably-arresting-emma-watson-josh-gad-bill-condon|archivedate=April 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\nChris Nashawaty of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the film a B-, writing that the new songs were \"not transporting\". He felt the film needed more life and depth, but praised Watson's performance as the \"one of the film's stronger elements\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/03/03/beauty-and-the-beast-ew-review/|title=Beauty and the Beast: EW review|author=Chris Nashawaty|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=April 26, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910203044/http://ew.com/movies/2017/03/03/beauty-and-the-beast-ew-review/|archivedate=September 10, 2017}}</ref> Dana Schwartz of ''[[The New York Observer]]'' felt that some of the characters, such as Gaston and the Beast, had been watered down from the 1991 film, and that the additional backstory elements failed to \"advance the plot or theme in any meaningful way\" while adding considerable bloat. Schwartz considered the singing of the cast to be adequate but felt that their voices should have been dubbed over, especially for the complex songs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://observer.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-changes-dan-stevens-emma-watson/ |title=How 'Beauty and the Beast' Characters Changed from 1991 to 2017 |accessdate=September 1, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170910203128/http://observer.com/2017/03/beauty-and-the-beast-changes-dan-stevens-emma-watson/ |archivedate=September 10, 2017  }}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[90th Academy Awards|Academy Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| March 4, 2018\n| [[Academy Award for Best Production Design|Best Production Design]]\n| [[Sarah Greenwood]] and [[Katie Spencer]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/list-2018-oscar-nominations-1202668757/ |title=Oscar Nominations 2018: The Complete List |last=Staff |first=Variety |date=January 23, 2018 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=January 23, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123140604/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/list-2018-oscar-nominations-1202668757/ |archive-date=January 23, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n| [[Jacqueline Durran]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Art Directors Guild Awards 2017|Art Directors Guild Awards]]\n| January 27, 2018\n| [[Art Directors Guild Award for Excellence